<PB REF="00000045.tif" N="1">
<HEAD>I. Kindheit Jesu<LB>aus Ms. Laud 108.</HEAD>

<PB REF="00000046.tif">

<PB REF="00000047.tif">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Jci comence le enfaunce <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> crist.</HEAD>
<L><B>JN</B> &thorn;e honuraunce of swete <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>,<MILESTONE N="11" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;at is louerd ful of vertu,</L>
<L>Ane partie ichulle eou rede</L>
<L>Of is lijf and of is child hede;</L>
<L N="5">Nou ich eou bidde at &thorn;e biguynninge</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e herknen to &thorn;is talkinge,</L>
<L>&yogh;if &yogh;e it wulleth under stonde:</L>
<L>Hov <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> liuede in &thorn;isse londe,</L>
<L>Ane partie &yogh;e mouwen i here;</L>
<L N="10">Herkniez &thorn;anne alle i fere.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> crist was i bore,</L>
<L>To saui &thorn;is world &thorn;at was for lore,</L>
<L>In one Crachche he was i leid</L>
<L>Bi fore Oxe and Asse; soth&thorn; it is seid:</L>
<L N="15">Wel huy wusten in heore mod</L>
<L>&thorn;at it was <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> verrei god,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at he was into eor&thorn;e i send</L>
<L>To bringue us out of turment.</L>
<L>And seth&thorn;e i circumcised was he,</L>
<L N="20">Ase &thorn;e lawe was in &thorn;at contre.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e temple &thorn;anne he was i sent,</L>
<L>He was welcome verreiement</L>
<L>Of symeon &thorn;at Man old,</L>
<L>&thorn;at muche of him bi fore hadde i told.</L>
<L N="25">&thorn;er after &thorn;re kinges of vncou&thorn;e londe</L>
<L>To &thorn;at child brou&yogh;ten heore sonde.</L>
<L>Inou&yogh;h &yogh;e habbez &thorn;arof i heord telle:</L>
<L>Ne kepe ich more of heom spelle.</L>
<L>Bote &thorn;o Heroude &thorn;at wicke king</L>
<L N="30">Hadde i heord &thorn;at ti&thorn;ing
<PB REF="00000048.tif" N="4"></L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;is kingues of oneku&thorn;e contreie</L>
<L>Werent i wend hom bi an o&thorn;er wei&yogh;e,</L>
<L>Him &thorn;ou&yogh;hte is herte wolde to breke,</L>
<L>Bote &yogh;if &thorn;at he were a wreke.</L>
<L N="35">For Jesus loue he let sle</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e children of &thorn;at contre</L>
<L>Of two &yogh;er elde and of more;</L>
<L>He was Man of wicke lore.</L>
<L>He &thorn;at made &thorn;is world of nou&yogh;t</L>
<L N="40">Swi&thorn;e wel wuste is wicke &thorn;ou&yogh;t;</L>
<L>Nolde he nou&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;e maistrie</L>
<L>Hedde heroude with his enuie.</L>
<L>Almi&yogh;hti king is Aungel hende</L>
<L>To Marie he gan sende</L>
<L N="45">And to Josep hire housebonde,</L>
<L>And bad heom wende into egypte londe</L>
<L>And &thorn;are bi leue for to eft sone</L>
<L>&thorn;at o&thorn;ur ty&thorn;ingues to heom come.</L>
<L>&thorn;o Marie and Josep hadden i heorde &thorn;is sonde,</L>
<L N="50">Ne dwelden huy nou&yogh;t after ful longue,</L>
<L>Huy token with heom &thorn;at neod was,</L>
<L>Ase to heom bi feol in &thorn;at cas,</L>
<L>Huy duden heom bliue in &thorn;e weie,</L>
<L>As &thorn;e Aungel heom gan sei&yogh;e.</L>
<L N="55">Ne hadden huy nou&yogh;t ful longue i fare,</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy ne sei&yogh;en wondres &thorn;are:</L>
<L>&thorn;e Bestes Mankene and eke wilde</L>
<L>Comen out of wodes and of felde;</L>
<L>&thorn;e Dragouns out of &thorn;e Montaygne</L>
<L N="60">Comen ful Manie bi on and tweine</L>
<L>To herien him &thorn;at &thorn;are was lad,</L>
<L>Him to seon huy weren ful glad;</L>
<L>&thorn;e liouns kene and eke grete</L>
<L>&thorn;at swete child huy gonnen mete,</L>
<L N="65">&thorn;e wolfues &thorn;at weren ramage</L>
<L>To &thorn;at child of so &yogh;oung age</L>
<L>Fullen on knes and to him bouwe</L>
<L>And in heore manere on him lowe.
<PB REF="00000049.tif" N="5"></L>
<L>&thorn;e Dragouns of grete fli&yogh;hte</L>
<L N="70">To &thorn;at child ful of mi&yogh;hte</L>
<L>Ali&yogh;hten heom lowe to &thorn;e grounde</L>
<L>And bi leften a wel gret stounde,</L>
<L>Him forto honoure &thorn;at hem wrou&yogh;hte.</L>
<L>Marie was in wel grete &thorn;ou&yogh;te;</L>
<L N="75">Heo was a gast and in feringue,</L>
<L>For it was so muche a&yogh;ein kuynde</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e wolf wilde and rauisaunt</L>
<L>With &thorn;e schep &yogh;eode so milde so lomb,</L>
<L>And ne made to heom no semblaunt</L>
<L N="80">To don heom harm taunt ne quaunt.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> quaunt <I>mit danebengeschriebenem</I> kaunt <I>von ders. Hand.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e wel ech it onder stod</L>
<L>&thorn;at it was soth&thorn; &thorn;at seide &thorn;e bok,</L>
<L>&thorn;at ysaie to folke seide,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he &thorn;e prophecie gan schewe and rede;</L>
<L N="85">He seide wel with heorte mild:</L>
<L>&thorn;at, &yogh;wane Marie bere a child,</L>
<L>&thorn;e wolf with &thorn;e schep scholde ete<NOTE PLACE="foot">e <I>in</I> ete <I>scheint ausradirt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>With outen harm with oute hete.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here ore leuedi a li&yogh;hte of &thorn;e Asse, and Josep hire halp a doun, &amp; made hire sitte onder a treo for hete &thorn;at bar apples and o&thorn;er fruyt.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;ene &thorn;ridde dai verreiment</L>
<L N="90">&thorn;at huy weren out i went</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at corsede lond</L>
<L>&thorn;at heroudes hadde in is hond,</L>
<L>&thorn;e sonne wax hot and snov&yogh;h bri&yogh;ht,</L>
<L>Ase it was &thorn;oru&yogh;h godes mi&yogh;ht;</L>
<L N="95">And Marie &thorn;at swete Maide</L>
<L>clepede Josep and to him sayde:</L>
<L>Sire Josep, wite &thorn;ou for soth&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;is hete gret dere me doth&thorn;,
<PB REF="00000050.tif" N="6"></L>
<L>&thorn;ere fore me &thorn;incheth&thorn; it is &thorn;e beste</L>
<L N="100">vnder &thorn;is trco &thorn;at ich me reste.</L>
<L>Dame, he seide, at &thorn;i wille it beo!</L>
<L>Josep hire ladde to &thorn;at treo</L>
<L>And of &thorn;at best &thorn;at heo sat on</L>
<L>Softeliche haf hire a doun</L>
<L N="105">And bad hire sitte and reste &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Forte &thorn;e hete i passede were.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here &thorn;at treo beu&yogh; a doun &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;e voiz of <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>, and Marie eat of &thorn;at fruyt, &thorn;at heo muche desiredc. and heo &yogh;af Josepe &thorn;ar of ase muche ase he wolde.</HEAD>
<L>VNder &thorn;at treo hire reste Marie</L>
<L>Wuch heo bi heold with hire ei&yogh;e;</L>
<L>Gret wille heo hadde to habbe &thorn;ar</L>
<L N="110">Of &thorn;at fruyt &thorn;at it bar.</L>
<L>Wel heo schewede in hire willing</L>
<L>&thorn;at heo &thorn;er to hadde liking,</L>
<L>And seide to Josep with lei&yogh;hinde wille:</L>
<L>Jcholde ich hadde here of mi fulle.</L>
<L N="115"><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;at wuste heore &thorn;ou&yogh;t i liche</L>
<L>To &thorn;at treo spak mildeliche</L>
<L>And seide: ich &thorn;e hote, treo,</L>
<L>To mi Moder a bouwe &thorn;ou &thorn;e!</L>
<L>With gret plente nou&thorn;e &yogh;if hire</L>
<L N="120">Of &thorn;at fruit &thorn;at &thorn;ou dest bere!</L>
<L>To &thorn;at voiz with gret de duyt</L>
<L>&thorn;at treo a beu&yogh; &thorn;at bar &thorn;at fruyt.</L>
<L>Marie inou&yogh;h &thorn;ar of et,</L>
<L>And al so dude Josep ek.</L>
<L N="125">&thorn;o huy weren wel i fuld</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at fruyt erore wild,</L>
<L>&thorn;arof huy maden ful gret blisse</L>
<L>And &thorn;onkeden <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> for is godnesse.</L>
<L>Muche loued is Moder Jesu,</L>
<L N="130">For he dude for hire muche vertu,
<PB REF="00000051.tif" N="7"></L>
<L>And heo louedde him, and &thorn;at was ri&yogh;th,</L>
<L>For him heo was bo&thorn;e fair and briht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here comaunde <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;at treo stonde upri&yogh;ht, &thorn;o is moder hadde inou&yogh; i&yogh;ete.</HEAD>
<L>JEsu Crist &thorn;at blessede child,</L>
<L>&thorn;at to is Moder was so mild,</L>
<L N="135">Blessede &thorn;at treo with is honde</L>
<L>And het it upri&yogh;ht forto stonde.</L>
<L>With oute ani more lette</L>
<L>&thorn;at treo ful sone upri&yogh;ht him sette</L>
<L>And stod also ase hit dude er.</L>
<L N="140">&thorn;is merueile he dude &thorn;er.</L>
<L>Gret Joye &thorn;anne ore lauedi hadde</L>
<L>Of hire sone &thorn;at heo ladde,</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e dedes &thorn;at he wrou&yogh;te,</L>
<L>Ful gret wonder &thorn;ar of heom &thorn;ou&yogh;te.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here comaundede <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> &thorn;at treo &thorn;at wellene sprounguen out is Rotene, and it bi feol &thorn;at Marie and Josep &thorn;erof dronken.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at wellene <I>im Ms. doppelt.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<L N="145">&THORN;O seide Joseph &thorn;at olde Man:</L>
<L>Marie, mi leof, mi swete lefman,</L>
<L>&thorn;urst me takez and water me failez,</L>
<L>Ne can ime nou&yogh;t &thorn;ar of conseile.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne answerede ore leuedi</L>
<L N="150">And seide: sore a &thorn;urst am J,</L>
<L>And also &thorn;e Asse &thorn;at stondez here</L>
<L>So is a &thorn;urst on hire manere.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;at child, &thorn;at was &thorn;o so &yogh;ing,</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e i heorde here pleyning.</L>
<L N="155">Heorkniez hou seide &thorn;at swete wi&yogh;ht</L>
<L>To &thorn;at treo &thorn;at stod upri&yogh;ht:</L>
<L>Treo, ich &thorn;e comaunde and hote</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;are springe out of &thorn;ine Rote
<PB REF="00000052.tif" N="8"></L>
<L>Welle stremes faire and clere</L>
<L N="160">For mi Moder and for hire fere,</L>
<L>For ich ire louie and habbe deore;</L>
<L>Do nou, treo, ase ich &thorn;e lere,</L>
<L>And &yogh;uyt ich &thorn;e comaundi, treo,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou heonne forth&thorn;e ward beo</L>
<L N="165">Fruyt berinde in paradis</L>
<L>Jn Min orchard with oute mis,</L>
<L>And multepliinde &thorn;at &thorn;ou beo</L>
<L>Of racines &thorn;at comieth of &thorn;e,</L>
<L>&thorn;at wellene springuen out of &thorn;i rote<MILESTONE N="12" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="170">With watur cler guod and swote.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist ful of guodnesse</L>
<L>Hadde i seid wordes &thorn;usse,</L>
<L>Wellene clere in luyte stounde</L>
<L>Out of &thorn;e Rotene &thorn;are beoth i sprounge.</L>
<L N="175">&thorn;o dronk Marie al hire fulle</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e williche of &thorn;at welle,</L>
<L>And Josep also &thorn;at i wilned it hadde</L>
<L>In his &thorn;ou&yogh;t he was ful glad,</L>
<L>And Josep maude al so gret feste,</L>
<L N="180">More him likede &thorn;at ilke giste</L>
<L>&thorn;ane ani flechs i sode o&thorn;ur i rost.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> he &thorn;onkede alre most</L>
<L>Of al &thorn;at he heom dude er and &thorn;o.</L>
<L>Muche louede ore lauedi hire sone &thorn;o.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam an Aungel and tok &thorn;reo braunches of &thorn;at treo and sette heom in paradis, and alle &thorn;ulke &thorn;at &thorn;are bi side stoden weren ase huy weren dede for &thorn;e grete bri&yogh;htnesse &thorn;at huy i sei&yogh;en, and <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> confortede heom with is wordes.</HEAD>
<L N="185">TO &thorn;is treo &yogh;eot eft sone</L>
<L>Spak <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> godes sone:</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e braunches &thorn;at &thorn;ou berst i wis</L>
<L>Schullen beon set in paradys.</L>
<L>An Aungel wel sone cam
<PB REF="00000053.tif" N="9"></L>
<L N="190">And of &thorn;e braunches &thorn;are he nam,</L>
<L>In paradys huy weren sette,</L>
<L>As <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist it hauede i hote.</L>
<L>Ake &yogh;wenne &thorn;e Aungel was i sei&yogh;e</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e folk of &thorn;at contreie,</L>
<L N="195">Ech on is side was in fcre</L>
<L>And in gret doute &thorn;ei were;</L>
<L>Li&yogh;htnesse &thorn;are was so muche i sei&yogh;e</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;at treo &thorn;ar mide was wri&yogh;e</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e bi hinde and bi fore,</L>
<L N="200">&thorn;at no man mi&yogh;hte no for&thorn;ore</L>
<L>Of heom &thorn;at se &thorn;is vertues,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at <I>wol statt</I> &thorn;er <I>verschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ake fullen a doun ase dede cwes,</L>
<L>Ne seien huy neuere swuch bri&yogh;htnesse.</L>
<L>Muche huy &thorn;onkeden <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> of blisse.</L>
<L N="205">&thorn;anne spac <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> to hem:</L>
<L>&yogh;wi were &yogh;e so dredfule men?</L>
<L>Ful wel i wite &yogh;e it schulle,</L>
<L>&thorn;at mine hestes wor&thorn;eth ri&yogh;t folfullde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here &yogh;eode <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> into one temple of giwes and for dude heore Maumates, and alle huy fullen bi heom sulf, and &thorn;e feon|des &thorn;at with inne heom weren wenden out, &yogh;wuche heroudes &thorn;e king honourede with &thorn;e giwes.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O spac Josep to <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Die Initiale ist hier f&auml;lschlich</I> V <I>statt</I> &thorn;.</NOTE></L>
<L N="210">&thorn;at was ful of vertu:</L>
<L>Grete hete habbe we,</L>
<L>&thorn;at we fur brenneth&thorn;, so &thorn;inchez me,</L>
<L>And &yogh;if it is &thorn;i swete wille,</L>
<L>Go we ner &thorn;e weie stille,</L>
<L N="215">For it is caldore ner &thorn;e se,</L>
<L>Ore sped schal &thorn;e more beo.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> answerede with milde herte:</L>
<L>Ore wei schal nou&thorn;e sone schorte
<PB REF="00000054.tif" N="10"></L>
<L>&yogh;e bi &thorn;ritti guode Jorneies;</L>
<L N="220">It schal be soth &thorn;at ich eou sei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;o <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde &thorn;is wordes i seid oute,</L>
<L>Josep loke him a boute:</L>
<L>&thorn;e Montaynes &thorn;at weren hei&yogh;e</L>
<L>Of Egypte he sai&yogh;h with is ei&yogh;e,</L>
<L N="225">&thorn;at huy heom hadden i passed sone and wel</L>
<L>&thorn;oru&yogh; <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Marie sone echdel.</L>
<L>Bote gret wonder &thorn;arof huy hadde,</L>
<L>Hou huy so muche hadde i spedde.</L>
<L>In &thorn;ulke londe him &thorn;ou&yogh;te he sai&yogh;h</L>
<L N="230">Wickede men of false lai&yogh;h,</L>
<L>&thorn;at to &thorn;e fende weren i take</L>
<L>And heore beden to him make,</L>
<L>Ase &thorn;e prophecie seith, ich onder stonde:</L>
<L>Nei&yogh;h &thorn;reo hondret &thorn;are weren i founde</L>
<L N="235">Of false ymages i maked with honde,</L>
<L>In here temples forto stonde.</L>
<L>&thorn;udere comen al &thorn;at folk,</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lewede and eke clerk,</L>
<L>For to herien &thorn;ane feond</L>
<L N="240">&thorn;at hadde i bounde heom with is bend;</L>
<L>And heroudes &thorn;e king was &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Heriende heom ase huy godes weren.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist marie sone</L>
<L>Bi &thorn;at Maumerie gan come</L>
<L N="245">&thorn;at was i maud al of tricherie;</L>
<L>&thorn;ar of he felde a gret partie;</L>
<L>At&thorn;e temple <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> eode Jn</L>
<L>And lokede al a boute him,</L>
<L>Hov &thorn;are alle &thorn;ulke Men</L>
<L N="250">To &thorn;e false godes honoureden heom.</L>
<L>Bote &thorn;o <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> in i come was,</L>
<L>&thorn;are was soruwe and alas:</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at synagogerie</L>
<L>It ful a doun, &thorn;at folk gan crie,</L>
<L N="255">Alle heore godus up and doun</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy honoureden fullen a non,
<PB REF="00000055.tif" N="11"></L>
<L>&thorn;e false ymages bi gunne to breke</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e feondes weren inne i steke.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam heroudes &thorn;e king of egypte lond and criede ore louerd merci and bad for &yogh;iuenesse of is wicke dedes, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> it him grauntede and to his folke, and &thorn;er to is beneiscoun.</HEAD>
<L>HEroudes, &thorn;o he hadde &thorn;is iherd,</L>
<L N="260">In his heorte he was a ferd,</L>
<L>For is godes he was sori</L>
<L>And for is folk also witterli.</L>
<L>Ake seth&thorn;e &thorn;o he wel vnder stod</L>
<L>&thorn;at swete <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> milde of mod</L>
<L N="265">Was mi&yogh;hti king and poustifs</L>
<L>And destruyde is enemis,</L>
<L>Of &yogh;wam &thorn;e prophetes tolden with toungue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> pphetes <I>ohne Zeichen der Abk&uuml;rzung</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And in write of him soungue</L>
<L>&thorn;e dedes &thorn;at <ABBR>ihus</ABBR> &thorn;are wrou&yogh;hte,</L>
<L N="270">Hit was wilninde in is &thorn;ou&yogh;te:</L>
<L>Pharaon &thorn;at was Aumperour</L>
<L>Of egypte with muche honour,</L>
<L>He nolde i leue for none lore</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> on eor&thorn;e wolde beo bore,</L>
<L N="275">Ne he nolde merci crie</L>
<L>For nou&yogh;t &thorn;at he sai&yogh;h with ei&yogh;e;</L>
<L>Bote pruyte he hauntede euere faste;</L>
<L>In &thorn;e se he Dreinte at&thorn;e laste</L>
<L>And to helle wende he,</L>
<L N="280">&thorn;are he schal euere be.</L>
<L>Heroudes was ai in doute,</L>
<L>And so is come with grete route</L>
<L>To <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;at childe so swete,</L>
<L>Hise sunnes forto bete.</L>
<L N="285">Jhesus of him hadde reu&thorn;e</L>
<L>And wuste his &thorn;ou&yogh;t and is treu&thorn;e,
<PB REF="00000056.tif" N="12"></L>
<L>His misdedes he for &yogh;af him sone</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;ei &thorn;at with him come.</L>
<L>Jesus is ful of for &yogh;iuenesse,</L>
<L N="290">So ful of loue and of blisse,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he fur &yogh;iuez is wrath&thorn;ing</L>
<L>To heom &thorn;at mis doth ani &thorn;ing,</L>
<L>And huy wollen with hore talent</L>
<L>Comen to amendement.</L>
<L N="295">&thorn;anne it is guod bo&thorn;e loude and stille</L>
<L>For to don al his wille,</L>
<L>For &thorn;at he wole is Joye him &yogh;iue</L>
<L>&thorn;at serueth him &thorn;e &yogh;wuyle he liueth;</L>
<L>&thorn;anne it is guod and sikernesse</L>
<L N="300">For to wurche to habbe blisse.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here compasede <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> &thorn;e seue lawes and dude watur &thorn;are with inne. Ake a feolun giw him lette with is staf and fur|dude is lawes, and &thorn;are fore he deide a non ri&yogh;ht &thorn;ere.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;Is was &thorn;e fifte &yogh;er</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> was i bore on eor&thorn;e her:</L>
<L>With o&thorn;ur children of &thorn;e cite</L>
<L>Him for to plei&yogh;e &thorn;anne eode he.</L>
<L N="305">&thorn;e children maden gret solas</L>
<L>As &thorn;ei &yogh;eoden in heore pas.</L>
<L>Huy wenden forth to &thorn;e Riuer,</L>
<L>&thorn;are huy founden &thorn;at watur cler.</L>
<L>Bote <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> fol of pouste</L>
<L N="310">Made &thorn;at watur drawe a&yogh;e;</L>
<L>&thorn;anne <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> ful of mi&yogh;hte and grace</L>
<L>Cumpassede a druye place,</L>
<L>Watur &thorn;are with inne he brou&yogh;te,</L>
<L>His lawes maken &thorn;are inne he &thorn;ou&yogh;te.</L>
<L N="315">Bote a giw of heorte wrac</L>
<L>Alle hise lawes &thorn;are he to brac.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> him seide with hastiue wille:</L>
<L>A &thorn;ou feondes sone of helle,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> sone doppelt.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000057.tif" N="13"></L>
<L>&yogh;wi hast &thorn;ou to broke mi lay?</L>
<L N="320">&thorn;ou schalt dei&yogh;e nou to day.</L>
<L>&thorn;o <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde &thorn;is word i seid,</L>
<L>&thorn;e giv to grounde ful doun ded;</L>
<L>&thorn;is o&thorn;ure nadden of him no plawe;</L>
<L>Ech wende fram o&thorn;ur in a &thorn;rowe</L>
<L N="325">And tolden heore faderes &thorn;is ilke cas</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;oru <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> heore fere ded was.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam Marie to hire sone and tolde him hov &thorn;e giwes &thorn;retneden Josep for &thorn;e childe &thorn;at was ded, &thorn;at with him and with o&thorn;ure pleide, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> touchede hine seth&thorn;e mid is fot.</HEAD>
<L>TO heore faderes lasse and more<MILESTONE N="13" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;is children come with grete fare</L>
<L>And seiden &thorn;us with wicke sawe</L>
<L N="330">&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde a child a slawe.</L>
<L>&thorn;eos giwes with heorte feint</L>
<L>To Josepe eoden to maken pleint,</L>
<L>And seiden wel with wicke breth</L>
<L>&thorn;at he was retet of &thorn;at deth.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms. deutlich</I> recet; <I>jedenfalls ist daf&uuml;r</I> retet <I>zu lesen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="335">With wordes bolde and eke kete</L>
<L>Josep &thorn;o huy gunne &thorn;rete.</L>
<L>&thorn;o was Josep in gret mourning</L>
<L>For &thorn;e giwene &thorn;retning.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;is seide Josep to Marie</L>
<L N="340">And: J ne dar <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> nou&yogh;t blamie.</L>
<L>&thorn;o Marie wuste of &thorn;is dede,</L>
<L>Hire sone heo wolde bidde and rede</L>
<L>&thorn;at he wolde for hire loue</L>
<L>Don so non more and lete &thorn;e wone.</L>
<L N="345">&thorn;o spac <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> to is moder dere:</L>
<L>Ich &thorn;e louie in eche manere;</L>
<L>Ich gan make here in mi lawe</L>
<L>A luytel watur a&yogh;ein with drawe,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne cometh&thorn; &thorn;es giv felonet
<PB REF="00000058.tif" N="14"></L>
<L N="350">And is staf with inne hath set,</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at i bigan to make</L>
<L>With is staf he gan it breke;</L>
<L>&thorn;are fore, dame, ich reherce &thorn;is</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou it wite he dude amis,</L>
<L N="355">&thorn;ere fore &thorn;is feolun is here ded;</L>
<L>Ake lif him tit &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;i red;</L>
<L>Moder, for &thorn;i loue here</L>
<L>Fram de&thorn;e to liue ichulle him a rere;</L>
<L>I nelle nou&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;ou habbe maugre</L>
<L N="360">In none stude, Moder, for me.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;at child milde of mod</L>
<L>Touche &thorn;ene dede with is fot,</L>
<L>And he a ros anon with &thorn;at,</L>
<L>Bote no merci he ne bad.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here made <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> twelf fliene of clei&yogh; with inne &thorn;e lawes and het heom fleon a mong hem alle.</HEAD>
<L N="365">Seth&thorn;e is <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> i wend a &yogh;e</L>
<L>To is lawes, ase i sei&yogh;e &thorn;e,</L>
<L>And of &thorn;e clei&yogh; &thorn;at he fond</L>
<L>He schop twelf fliene in &thorn;at lond.</L>
<L>&thorn;is dude he on a satur day.</L>
<L N="370">&thorn;e giwes come and &thorn;at i sai&yogh;h,</L>
<L>On cam &thorn;ere with gret espleit,</L>
<L>Ake sone he was a freid,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he wuste is dede,</L>
<L>Ful smartliche a&yogh;ein he eode</L>
<L N="375">And orn to Josep with oute let</L>
<L>And made to him plainte gret</L>
<L>And opbraid him of is sone</L>
<L>And seide he hadde vuele wone,</L>
<L>Muche him blamede, and &thorn;at wel ofte,</L>
<L N="380">For &thorn;at he in ontyme wrou&yogh;hte;</L>
<L>Ore lawes he al to rent</L>
<L>And bi sabat ore folk schent.
<PB REF="00000059.tif" N="15"></L>
<L>Josep to <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> eode in &thorn;e stude</L>
<L>And axede him &yogh;wi bi sabat he so dude.</L>
<L N="385"><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> to gadere is hondene smot</L>
<L>And lou&yogh;h so &thorn;at it dude him guod</L>
<L>And seide: fliene, forth fleo &yogh;e,</L>
<L>&yogh;wodere &thorn;at owere wille it beo!</L>
<L>&thorn;o flouwen forth &thorn;ulke fli&yogh;en</L>
<L N="390">Bi fore him and o&thorn;ur men.</L>
<L>Some &thorn;at sei&yogh;en &thorn;at merueile</L>
<L>&thorn;onkeden <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> with guode wille.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam a wickede giv and smot <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> vnder &thorn;e ere bi fore &thorn;e princes, and &thorn;e giv ful a doun to grounde, and &thorn;e princes wrath&thorn;eden heom to ward <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> and Josep.</HEAD>
<L>SOne &thorn;are comen o&thorn;ure alse<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms. urspr&uuml;nglich</I> also; o <I>ist in</I> e <I>verbessert</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>bi fore &thorn;e princes fikele and false</L>
<L N="395">And seiden anon with heore sawes</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> despisede heore lawes.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> a midde &thorn;e place stod,</L>
<L>And &thorn;are cam on of heorte wod,</L>
<L>On of &thorn;e princes hine bi &yogh;at,</L>
<L N="400">And <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> ful euele he smot;</L>
<L>Bote <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> him stod ful stille,</L>
<L>&thorn;at ilke stroc him likede ille;</L>
<L>Nou&yogh;ht for &thorn;an with oute lesing</L>
<L>Of him he tok gret wreching:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Im Ms. ist nicht zu unterscheiden, ob</I> wreching <I>oder</I> wrething <I>zu lesen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="405">He feol a doun ded &thorn;are a non</L>
<L>Bi fore heom alle euerchon.</L>
<L>&thorn;are fore was Josep in grete fering,</L>
<L>For huy him eoden alle &thorn;retning.
<PB REF="00000060.tif" N="16"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here a giv lep up to <ABBR>Jhues</ABBR> scholdren and smot <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> vuele, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> him wrath&thorn;ede and &thorn;e giv ful a doun ded to grounde a non.</HEAD>
<L>JOscp for doute of &thorn;e men</L>
<L N="410">Ladde <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> with him hom,</L>
<L>For euerechone &thorn;ulke giwes</L>
<L>Hateden muche swete Jesus.</L>
<L>Ano&thorn;ur giv is aftur i rounne,</L>
<L>Bi fore alle o&thorn;ure he was &thorn;anne,</L>
<L N="415">Opon <ABBR>Jhues</ABBR> scholdren he lep up &thorn;ere</L>
<L>And smot him vuele onder &thorn;e ere.</L>
<L>Jhesus with oute more to telle</L>
<L>cleopede him &thorn;e feondes sone of helle,</L>
<L>And seide: henne ne gost &thorn;ou hol ne fier,</L>
<L N="420">Here &thorn;e worth encombrer.</L>
<L>He ful a doun ded for is gult,</L>
<L>Ne hadde he no&thorn;ur dunt ne pult.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cometh &thorn;e giwes to Josep and makez gret plainte of <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> for he hadde a child a slawe; ake seth&thorn;e <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hine a rerde.</HEAD>
<L>Aftur al &thorn;isilke sake</L>
<L>gret noise huy guonne make,</L>
<L N="425">&thorn;e giwes into al &thorn;e londe,</L>
<L>And seiden man dude hem gret schonde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms. anscheinend</I> hom, <I>aus</I> ham <I>verbessert; es ist aber wol</I> hem <I>zu lesen.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Alle &thorn;eos giwes lowe and proute</L>
<L>Of <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> Messie huy hadden doute</L>
<L>And to Marie heom playnieth &thorn;ore,</L>
<L N="430">Bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lasse and eke &thorn;e more,</L>
<L>And hotez and biddez wel Marie</L>
<L>&thorn;at heo schulle hire sone chastie.</L>
<L>Marie and Josep to <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> sede</L>
<L>And ful ofte si&thorn;es him bede
<PB REF="00000061.tif" N="17"></L>
<L N="435">Bi fore &thorn;e princes &thorn;at &thorn;er were,</L>
<L>With faire wordes huy guonne him lere.</L>
<L>&thorn;o speken &thorn;is maistres gret:</L>
<L>Josep, &thorn;ou art mis bi hed;</L>
<L>Tac us to lere &thorn;inne sone,</L>
<L N="440">And he schal lete is vuele wone;</L>
<L>His Maister schal beo Zacharie,</L>
<L>&thorn;at him schal techen of clergie;</L>
<L>Al ore lawe he hauez ouer herd,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> ore <I>doppelt.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Of him he may beo wel i lered.</L>
<L N="445">Josep bad <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> ful &yogh;eorne</L>
<L>&thorn;at he scholde of heom leorne,</L>
<L>Ake ase ich wene he nolde go</L>
<L>Anne fot with heom &thorn;o.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne spac on a rebous:</L>
<L N="450">Josep, &thorn;i sone is Merueilous;</L>
<L>He hauez don us more lore</L>
<L>&thorn;ane euere us dude ani bi fore:</L>
<L>A giv he haueth a slawe i wis</L>
<L>&thorn;at was i holde of gret pris;</L>
<L N="455">To his freont make &thorn;i gre,</L>
<L>O&thorn;ur &thorn;ou worst i flem of &thorn;is contre;</L>
<L>For &yogh;if &yogh;e duellez here ou&yogh;t longer,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> long' <I>d. i.</I> longer.</NOTE></L>
<L>He wole don us muche wrong.</L>
<L>Ake &yogh;if he wolde drawe him &thorn;are fro,</L>
<L N="460">It were guod to bidde him so.</L>
<L>Josep preide Marie suete</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> wolde is noise lete,</L>
<L>And Marie a non hire sone bad.</L>
<L>Moder, he seide, ich am glad</L>
<L N="465">&thorn;ine hestes forto do.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> to &thorn;e dede giv gan go,</L>
<L>&thorn;ane giv hente bi &thorn;enere,</L>
<L>Fram deth to liue he gan him a rere.</L>
<L>Aris up, he seide, &thorn;ou cheitif!</L>
<L N="470">&thorn;e giv a ros and hadde lif.
<PB REF="00000062.tif" N="18"></L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> fram him stilleliche eode.</L>
<L>&thorn;at folk hadde wounder of &thorn;at dede.</L>
<L>Josep was glad in &thorn;is cas</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;is giv a liue was,</L>
<L N="475">For he was i &thorn;retned ofte</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at folk &thorn;at luyte of him rou&yogh;hte.</L>
<L>So was marie &thorn;at Maide mild</L>
<L>And <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hire swete child.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here was <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> i lad to scole and ouercam alle &thorn;e maistres with puyr clergie; so &thorn;at euerech heold him sulf amad, for he schewede heom wel &thorn;at huy weren out of ri&yogh;hte Muinde.</HEAD>
<L><B>A</B> Gret Maister Zacharie,</L>
<L N="480">&thorn;at muche cou&thorn;e of &thorn;at clergie,</L>
<L>To Josepe hadde gret enuie</L>
<L>And him seide: &thorn;ou dest folie</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou nelt lere &thorn;ine sone in londe</L>
<L>And lettre don him vnder stonde.</L>
<L N="485">Men him scholden take &yogh;eorne</L>
<L>And hine an hongue o&thorn;ur fur berne.</L>
<L>Josep seide: i &thorn;e bi seche,</L>
<L>Tak hine to &thorn;e and &thorn;ou him teche.</L>
<L>Nou spekth Jh&umacr;s wordes clere</L>
<L N="490">And answerez Zacharie &thorn;e grete maistere:</L>
<L>With wrong, maister, &thorn;ou seist me blame,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ar of ich habbe schame.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> ne bi lefte nou&yogh;t to longe</L>
<L>&thorn;at he ne gan with wordes strongue</L>
<L N="495">&thorn;ene Maister streite a posi,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ar to was he ful hardi;</L>
<L>Wel sone he axede him, in is boke</L>
<L>&yogh;wat it was &thorn;at he gan loke.</L>
<L>&thorn;ou lokest, maister, in &thorn;i lai,</L>
<L N="500">Wel ofte ich it i seo and feor ich sai;</L>
<L>And so ne canst &thorn;ou me nou&yogh;t telle,</L>
<L>&yogh;wat ich &thorn;enke ne &yogh;wat ich wille?</L>
<L>&thorn;ou wenest of lore &thorn;ou habbe mest
<PB REF="00000063.tif" N="19"></L>
<L>Of alle men, and hauest lest,</L>
<L N="505">Of alle &thorn;e lawes &thorn;ou hauest &thorn;at los</L>
<L>And honoured ase a god of &thorn;eos and &thorn;os:<NOTE PLACE="foot">art <I>fehlt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Canst &thorn;ou telle &yogh;wanne &thorn;ou were i bore?</L>
<L>Nai ich wene &thorn;ou hauest i lore;</L>
<L>To blame Josep &yogh;wi art&thorn;ou glad,</L>
<L N="510">&thorn;at me haueth hidere to &thorn;e i lad?</L>
<L>Vnder stond ane &yogh;wile hit:</L>
<L>Canst &thorn;ou telle &yogh;wat seith &thorn;et writ?</L>
<L>A god schal i bore beo</L>
<L>&thorn;at al schal warde and al ise;</L>
<L N="515">He is nou i bore, for so&thorn;e i sei&yogh;e,</L>
<L>And fale si&thorn;e &thorn;ou hast him i sei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Hou is it, &yogh;wat is &thorn;i &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou &thorn;at child ne knowest nou&yogh;t?</L>
<L>&thorn;o Zacharie him vnder stod</L>
<L N="520">And &thorn;is i heorde of &thorn;at child guod,</L>
<L>Ouer come him heold and i schend,</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;at &thorn;are stoden verreiement.</L>
<L>Hou mai &thorn;is beon, seide he,<NOTE PLACE="foot">n <I>in</I> beon <I>ist &uuml;bergeschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at swuch a child i bore mai be,</L>
<L N="525">And &thorn;ane ore Maister he can more</L>
<L>And herre wexeth nou&thorn;e in lore?</L>
<L>Vnder stondeth &thorn;anne, seide <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>:</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e wel &yogh;e it witeth some nou</L>
<L>&thorn;at Abraham was bi dawes olde,</L>
<L N="530">And for ore fader he was i holde,</L>
<L>And ovre eldore al so hadde</L>
<L>Of him i soungue and i radde;</L>
<L>&yogh;e loueden him with heorte and mod</L>
<L>And douteden him more &thorn;ane god;</L>
<L N="535">&thorn;ilke Abraham &thorn;at ich of telle,</L>
<L>Ich hine i sai, for lie ich nelle,</L>
<L>And ofte si&thorn;e with him I spac;</L>
<L>He me louez with oute lac.
<PB REF="00000064.tif" N="20"></L>
<L>To &thorn;at answerede a giv wild:</L>
<L N="540">&yogh;uyt neart&thorn;ov, he seide, bote a child!</L>
<L>And sone bi guynnest to make lesing,</L>
<L>&thorn;at we witen wel bi ovre heoring. &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">ovre <I>am Rande nebengeschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Seggeth forth al ower wille</L>
<L>And al &thorn;at &yogh;e konne telle!</L>
<L N="545">And &thorn;ou giv, &thorn;ou olde Man,</L>
<L>Ful vuele &thorn;ou me i knowe can;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> canst <I>mit unterpungirtem</I> st; st <I>soll also nicht gelten; die Form</I> can <I>2. sgl. ist aber eigenth&uuml;mlich</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bi fore Abraham ich was,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ou seist &thorn;at i nas;</L>
<L>Me &thorn;unchez, &yogh;e alle ne mowen nou&yogh;t se,</L>
<L N="550">&yogh;wane ich habbe here ofte i be</L>
<L>Among eov and i schewed ai</L>
<L>And amendet ouwer lai.</L>
<L>&thorn;es giv him heold ouer come</L>
<L>And &thorn;is Maistres euerch one;</L>
<L N="555">Non nolde &thorn;are more dwelle,</L>
<L>For <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> with resun heom gan felle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here lep Jesus fram on hul to an o&thorn;ur, and &thorn;e children wolden do also, and alle huy breke heore neckene bote o child.</HEAD>
<L>SOne &thorn;are after nou&yogh;ht longue it nas,</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> wente in is pas</L>
<L>With &yogh;oungue giwes &thorn;at he founde</L>
<L N="560">Swuy&thorn;e hei&yogh;e vp on &thorn;e Mounte.</L>
<L>To luppen alle huy weren prest,</L>
<L>Ake <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> him sulf lep alre furst</L>
<L>Fram hul to o&thorn;ur starc and gret,</L>
<L>And seth&thorn;e cuerech child aftur lep;</L>
<L N="565">Bote non ne mi&yogh;hte so fer luppe:</L>
<L>Adoun huy fullen and breke heore necke</L>
<L>O&thorn;ur heore leggus o&thorn;ur heore &thorn;i&yogh;h,<NOTE PLACE="foot">heore <I>im Ms. doppelt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>O&thorn;ur sum mishap so hadden huy;</L>
<L>So at&thorn;e laste dede huy were,
<PB REF="00000065.tif" N="21"></L>
<L N="570">&thorn;e giwes &thorn;at comen with him &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>In vuele tyme to heom it cam</L>
<L>For to luppe a &yogh;ein Jesum.</L>
<L>Ake o child &thorn;ere was &thorn;at luppe ne wolde,</L>
<L>So forto do Jhesus it nolde;</L>
<L N="575">&thorn;ilke louede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> i nou&yogh;</L>
<L>And ay &yogh;ware he &yogh;eode to him he drou&yogh;.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;at child lokede up on</L>
<L>And bad him stonde stille a non</L>
<L>And seide to him: bi lef &thorn;ou &thorn;er!</L>
<L N="580">&thorn;ou nast nou&yogh;t to done her.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here comen &thorn;e giwes to Josepe and seiden &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde heore children a slawe, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> heom arerde.</HEAD>
<L>Alle &thorn;e giwes euerech on</L>
<L>Dede weren bote &thorn;at on.</L>
<L>&thorn;is word bi gan wide springue,</L>
<L>And alle huy eoden <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;retninggue.</L>
<L N="585">Josep &thorn;e &yogh;uyt nas nou&yogh;t &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Ne Marie &thorn;ad Maide deore;</L>
<L>Nou&yogh;t for &thorn;an with envie</L>
<L>Echone gunne on him crie,</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes and &thorn;e maistres kete</L>
<L N="590">Gunne heom with wordes &thorn;rete;</L>
<L>And &thorn;are fore Marie &thorn;at Maide cler</L>
<L>Sou&yogh;te hire sone de boner</L>
<L>And founde hine plei&yogh;ind in is plei.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne seide &thorn;at swete mai:</L>
<L N="595">Mi leue sone, ich bidde &thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou haue of heom pite</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;eonde liggeth&thorn; dede &thorn;ere;</L>
<L>For mi loue &thorn;ou heom a rere!</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> louede is Moder deore</L>
<L N="600">And wel i heorde is moder preiere;</L>
<L>To &thorn;at Mount he gan gon</L>
<L>And &thorn;are he wrou&yogh;te Miracle a non:
<PB REF="00000066.tif" N="22"></L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes &thorn;at weren dede alle</L>
<L>A non ri&yogh;ht he gan heom calle,</L>
<L N="605">And seide: cometh hider to me!</L>
<L>&yogh;ware habbe &yogh;e &yogh;are i beo?</L>
<L>Alle huy a risen and to him come,</L>
<L>And <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> &thorn;o heom ladde sone</L>
<L>Bi fore is Moder &thorn;are heo stod,</L>
<L N="610">And heo was glad in hire mod.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e giwes &thorn;e grete ferrede</L>
<L>Wondreden of &thorn;at childes dede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here eode <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> and bar a picher and mo o&thorn;ur children with him to &thorn;e welle, so &thorn;at ane childes picher to brac, and forto a legge strif <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> it made a&yogh;en.</HEAD>
<L>To one welle fair and cler,</L>
<L>&thorn;at was nei&yogh;h a riuer,</L>
<L N="615"><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> eode for to fechche watur,</L>
<L>And giwene children feole to gadere</L>
<L>Him siweden to &thorn;at welle streme</L>
<L>For to fechchen watur clene.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> bi fore gan to &thorn;ruste</L>
<L N="620">For to habbe watur furste.</L>
<L>Ake on and o&thorn;ur &thorn;are a&yogh;en spac,</L>
<L>And in &thorn;at &thorn;rust a picher brac,</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hauede &thorn;udere i brou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes it breken with wicke &thorn;ou&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="625"><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR>, a luyte made him wroth&thorn;,</L>
<L>To maken strif him was loth&thorn;;</L>
<L>&thorn;e peces &thorn;at lei&yogh;en on &thorn;e grounde</L>
<L>To gadere he brou&yogh;hte in luyte stounde,</L>
<L>And seide: lo here &thorn;is picher &thorn;at &yogh;e breke</L>
<L N="630">Is hol and sound; with oute hete</L>
<L>Beoth&thorn; guode felawes with oute striue,</L>
<L>And alle wrath&thorn;es beon fur &yogh;iue!</L>
<L>Guode freond heo weren a non</L>
<L>Jhesus and &thorn;is children ech on.
<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="23"></L>
<L N="635">Ech hath is picher i fuld &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at welle with oute bere.</L>
<L>Jhesus liet hem heore wille</L>
<L>And is picher fulde al so.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hinter</I> wille <I>ist</I> do <I>im Ms. ausgelassen</I>.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here Jesus hangude is picher on &thorn;e sonne beme, and &thorn;e &yogh;ongue giwes wolden also, ake heore picheres fullen doun to grounde and breken euerechone, and gret wonder huy hadden &thorn;at his picher hieng so.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;E sonne was hot &thorn;at ilke dai.</L>
<L N="640">Jesus &thorn;ene sonne bem i sai:</L>
<L>His picher on &thorn;e sonne beme he hieng</L>
<L>With oute rop with oute streng.</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes wolden don also,</L>
<L>Heore pichers fullen and breken a two,</L>
<L N="645">For huy wenden in &thorn;at stude</L>
<L>To don al so Jesus dude.</L>
<L>Jesues picher hieng wel stille,</L>
<L>Ase it was is swete wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;at o child a non forth him wente</L>
<L N="650">And to &thorn;e elde giwes &thorn;e ti&thorn;inge sente</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e folk of &thorn;e cite he tolde,</L>
<L>Hov Jesues picher with outen holde</L>
<L>Hangude on &thorn;e sonne bem ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>With oute rope o&thorn;ur streng for so&thorn;e apli&yogh;ht,</L>
<L N="655">And hou heore picheres weren to broke,</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy ne mouwen don nonmore note.</L>
<L>Muche folk is &thorn;udere i orne</L>
<L>And &thorn;at picher bi holdeth &yogh;eorne,<MILESTONE N="15" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Hou it &thorn;are i hangued was,</L>
<L N="660">Faste huy bi heolden &thorn;at cas;</L>
<L>Euerech &thorn;at &thorn;e picher i sei&yogh;e</L>
<L>Hadde wonder hou it heng so hei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;et wonder was wide i told a boute</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e to lowe and to proute.
<PB REF="00000068.tif" N="24"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here beden &thorn;e children <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> &thorn;at he made heore pichers i hole, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> so dude and tok euerech is owene picher i hol, and eoden heom hom.</HEAD>
<L N="665">&THORN;Is children &yogh;eoden forth i fere</L>
<L>And beden <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> with milde chere:</L>
<L>&thorn;at he &thorn;e pichers ase huy &thorn;udere hem brou&yogh;te</L>
<L>Made hole a &yogh;ein, huy him bi sou&yogh;ten.</L>
<L>Jhesus blessede &thorn;e picheres a non:</L>
<L N="670">Al hole huy stoden up ech on.</L>
<L>Euerech hath hol is picher i founde</L>
<L>Ful of watur stondinde on grounde,</L>
<L>And ech on is picher sette is hond</L>
<L>&thorn;at bifore him wolde hanguy with wrong.</L>
<L N="675">Seth&thorn;e huy goth&thorn; heore picheres berinde</L>
<L>Hom ful of watur with oute lesinge.</L>
<L>Heore freondes huy tolden euerech grot,</L>
<L>Hou <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde imad euerechches pot.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here hudde a giv is child in an hous and bi lek hit faste, for it was i woned to gon with Jesu, and he nolde nou&yogh;t &thorn;at it more with him code.</HEAD>
<L>Nov of a child ichulle eov telle</L>
<L N="680">&thorn;at louede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> with is wille</L>
<L>And siwede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> in plei&yogh;ingue;</L>
<L>&thorn;are fore is fader him &yogh;af ofte &thorn;retninge.</L>
<L>To huyde is sone he hadde in Muynde,</L>
<L>&thorn;at Jesus him ne scholde finde;</L>
<L N="685">&thorn;at child wro&thorn;eliche he gan &thorn;rete</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;at he wolde him bete,</L>
<L>Bote he lete &thorn;e compaygnie</L>
<L>Of him &thorn;at i bore was of marie.</L>
<L>&thorn;at child weop sore and wrong is ei&yogh;e,</L>
<L N="690">For he ne moste with <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> plei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>He sai&yogh; &thorn;at for al is &thorn;rete<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms. urspr&uuml;nglich</I> &thorn;e; &thorn; <I>ist aber ausgestrichen und</I> h <I>von anderer Hand daneben geschrieben; zu lesen ist wol</I> &thorn;o he.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000069.tif" N="25"></L>
<L>&thorn;at child wepingue nolde lete:</L>
<L>With a &yogh;erde sore he it beot,</L>
<L>And euere &thorn;at child &thorn;e more weop.</L>
<L N="695">&yogh;eot to &thorn;at child spac &thorn;e giv:</L>
<L>&thorn;ou schalt for loue of Jesu</L>
<L>In a tour beo put, &yogh;if i mai,</L>
<L>Al &thorn;is ilke longue dai.</L>
<L>&thorn;at child he tok sone bi &thorn;e chin</L>
<L N="700">And ladde hine to &thorn;e prisone In,</L>
<L>In a tour starc and strong,</L>
<L>&thorn;ar on nas bote on in &yogh;ong;</L>
<L>&thorn;are inne him seolf &thorn;at child was</L>
<L>With oute mete and solas.</L>
<L N="705">&thorn;e fader swor &thorn;at he scholde</L>
<L>In &thorn;at tour ale gate beo holde.</L>
<L>&thorn;e fader eode forth and lefde him &thorn;ere</L>
<L>With a swi&thorn;e reufole chere,</L>
<L>And of &thorn;at tour he tok wit him &thorn;e kei&yogh;e</L>
<L N="710">And leide ire fer out of &thorn;e wei&yogh;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here tok Jesus &thorn;at child out of prisone, &thorn;are as it was for enchesun of him, ake <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> wuste wel al heore dedes and halp &thorn;at child.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus wuste al heore &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>And to longue ne bi lefde nou&yogh;t</L>
<L>&thorn;at he to &thorn;at child ne cam</L>
<L>And seide: felawe, here ich am,</L>
<L N="715">Ovt of a nuy to bringue &thorn;e,</L>
<L>In &yogh;wuche &thorn;ou art nou&thorn;e for me;</L>
<L>Tac me &thorn;i fingur a non ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>Ovt at &thorn;is hole, &yogh;if &thorn;ou mi&yogh;ht!</L>
<L>He spac and seide: a Jhesus ay,</L>
<L N="720">I ne wene nou&yogh;t &thorn;at i may:</L>
<L>&thorn;at hol is to narou&yogh; and to streit;</L>
<L>To comen out i ne can no red.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> seide: &yogh;wat hast &thorn;ou i seid?</L>
<L>&thorn;ou schalt come out with guod espleit.
<PB REF="00000070.tif" N="26"></L>
<L N="725">He pulte out is finguer &thorn;o,</L>
<L>And <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> hine drou sone him to.</L>
<L>Feble &thorn;ou art, and &thorn;at wel i se;</L>
<L>Ake nou&yogh;t for &thorn;an siwe &thorn;ou me!</L>
<L>&thorn;o <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hadde out i drawe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">him <I>fehlt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="730">&thorn;at child made muche plawe</L>
<L>And louede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> wel &thorn;e more,</L>
<L>&thorn;ane he dude er bi fore.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam &thorn;e giv to &thorn;e tour, &thorn;are he hadde idon &thorn;at child, and wende finde it &thorn;ere sore of hungred, and &thorn;o he no(!) fond him nou&yogh;t, he de maiede him sore and treuwede &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> hine hadde deliured.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O &thorn;at child was out of prisoun</L>
<L>&thorn;oru&yogh;h &thorn;e help of Jesum,</L>
<L N="735">Sone &thorn;are aftur is fader cam &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Swy&thorn;e wroth he was in is manere;</L>
<L>He geth&thorn; &thorn;e Dore to vnsteke,</L>
<L>And swy&thorn;e hei&yogh;e he gan to speke,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he is sone ne heorde nou&yogh;t</L>
<L N="740">And wide &yogh;ware hine hadde i sou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Swy&thorn;e wroth he was in is wille,</L>
<L>Him seolf he &thorn;ou&yogh;te forto spille,</L>
<L>For &thorn;at he wel vnder stod</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> hine hadde i brou&yogh;t out</L>
<L N="745">With ani cunnes enchauntement.</L>
<L>His bodi was &thorn;are fore in gret torment,</L>
<L>Ne mi&yogh;hte him helpe no solas:</L>
<L>For &thorn;at ilke wonder cas</L>
<L>&thorn;us was &thorn;e wrechche in Mourninge</L>
<L N="750">For is wicke bi lefingue.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here ladde Josep <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> to scole, and &thorn;e Maister hine aposede 
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="27"> and Jesus hine nolde answerie nou&yogh;t a word to &thorn;e Maistre of &thorn;e lawe.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> a a word, a <I>doppelt</I>.</NOTE></HEAD>
<L>&THORN;Is grete Maistres of clergie</L>
<L>To Marie comen with envie</L>
<L>And seiden to Josep and to Marie</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy duden gret folie,</L>
<L N="755">And ofte si&thorn;es huy gonne heom preie</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy duden him sette to clergie,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at huy hine token in alle wise</L>
<L>To Maister leowy &thorn;e wise.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e scole &thorn;ane cam <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR></L>
<L N="760">&thorn;at was ful of vertu.</L>
<L>Jesus hem grette in fair manere,</L>
<L>And maister leowi vnder feng him &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>And him he gan a posi;</L>
<L>Ake Jesus him nolde respoundi;</L>
<L N="765">Stille he stod bi fore him &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Nolde he no &thorn;ing him answere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here &thorn;e maister smot Jesum, and Jesus him wrath&thorn;ede and spak to heom sone afterwar ful heie wordes.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> nolde nou&yogh;t ansuere,</L>
<L>Maister leouwi dude him dere</L>
<L>And wax wroth&thorn; with <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> Marie sone,</L>
<L N="770">For he nolde for ei&yogh;e ne for loue</L>
<L>Answerien heom to heore resun;</L>
<L>For leowi wuste &thorn;at Jesum</L>
<L>Sotil was and wis of redes,</L>
<L>For he hadde ofte i heord is dedes,</L>
<L N="775">And fain wolde of him sum &thorn;ing i here,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he in resun &thorn;e wisore were;</L>
<L>Ake &thorn;o <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> nolde no &thorn;ing speke,</L>
<L>He &thorn;ou&yogh;te of him to beon a wreke:</L>
<L>With oute anie wordes mo</L>
<L N="780">He smot <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> a non ri&yogh;ht &thorn;o.
<PB REF="00000072.tif" N="28"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here hath&thorn; Jesus &thorn;e Maister ouer come with grete clergie, and bi fore heom &thorn;e sike i &yogh;iue hele of heore sicknesses, so &thorn;at alle ihole huy wenden fram him.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O wrath&thorn;ede him swete <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR></L>
<L>And seide to &thorn;at olde giv:</L>
<L>&yogh;wi hauest &thorn;ou i smite me &thorn;us?</L>
<L>Ful euele &thorn;ou knoust me i wis:</L>
<L N="785">I segge &thorn;e, &yogh;if &thorn;ou wolt it wite:</L>
<L>He &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast nou&thorn;e i smite</L>
<L>A &thorn;ousend si&thorn;e more can</L>
<L>&thorn;ane &thorn;ou and alle &thorn;is o&thorn;ur men.</L>
<L>Ful luyte wuyrth is al ower wit,</L>
<L N="790">Al for so&thorn;e i segge &thorn;it;</L>
<L>No guodnesse bi eou ine can,</L>
<L>Bote sum &yogh;e habbez &thorn;at fallez to man.</L>
<L>With ower maistrie &yogh;e me smite</L>
<L>And with hate and swi&thorn;e follike,</L>
<L N="795">Ake ne do &yogh;e non more &thorn;at folie,</L>
<L>Bote ansuerieth bi clergie!</L>
<L>To me ne mouwe &yogh;e &yogh;iue answere,</L>
<L>For &yogh;e ne wuteth &yogh;wat &thorn;e strenc&thorn;e bereth;</L>
<L>Tellez me nou&thorn;e in luyte stounde,</L>
<L N="800">&yogh;wi was Allef furst bi founde:</L>
<L>Of alle lettres he is &thorn;e furste,</L>
<L>And Beth&thorn; &thorn;at o&thorn;ur is &thorn;e nexte,</L>
<L>Gimel &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is of alle,</L>
<L>Deleth &thorn;e feor&thorn;e lettre is calle.</L>
<L N="805">&thorn;e Maister bi heold him, ase sat,</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;ht ase he were a mad,</L>
<L>And ofte is heorte gan to chaunge,</L>
<L>And to him spac wordes straunge:</L>
<L>Ho hauez i tei&yogh;ht &thorn;e so muche langage?</L>
<L N="810">&thorn;ou nart bote of &yogh;oung age.</L>
<L>Jesus answerede with ri&yogh;hte muynde:</L>
<L>He &thorn;at me tei&yogh;te is al weldinde;</L>
<L>He and ich with oute departing</L>
<L>Beoth&thorn; al on in alle &thorn;ing
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="29"></L>
<L N="815">And habben allon in pouste,<NOTE PLACE="foot">habben <I>wol statt</I> habbe ben <I>verschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And with oute ende so it schal be;</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou wolt ani more me knowe,<MILESTONE N="16" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ich &thorn;e may swi&thorn;e wel schewe</L>
<L>And axi &thorn;e wel mani a &thorn;ing,</L>
<L N="820">&thorn;at strong were to eov &thorn;e vndoing;</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at ich axede eov er,</L>
<L>Of Alleph Beth Gimel Deleth,</L>
<L>&yogh;if &yogh;e conne, ansueriez me nou&thorn;e</L>
<L>A non ri&yogh;ht with ouwer mou&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="825">Seggeth &yogh;wat ech lettre signefie,</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;at &yogh;e counne ou&yogh;t of clergie!</L>
<L>Ech lettre he tolde heom bi a counte,</L>
<L>Hou and &yogh;wat it wolde a mounte,</L>
<L>&thorn;e wit &thorn;ar of he vndude;</L>
<L N="830">Alle huy stoden stille in &thorn;at stude,</L>
<L>Ech &yogh;af &thorn;are to wel is lust</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at huy er nadden i wust.</L>
<L>&thorn;o seide Jesus to &thorn;e giwes:</L>
<L>A, &yogh;e wreches, &yogh;e chaitiues!</L>
<L N="835">Ne habbe &yogh;e i writen eouwer lawes,</L>
<L>&thorn;at beoth i maud &thorn;oru&yogh; mi sawes,</L>
<L>And &yogh;e ne conne nou&yogh;t answere,</L>
<L>&yogh;wat &thorn;is &thorn;ing wole a bere!</L>
<L>&yogh;e beoth blinde ase ich ou sei,</L>
<L N="840">For &yogh;e ne vnder stondez nou&yogh;t oure lei.</L>
<L>&thorn;o spac on of heom &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Loude with a sori bere:</L>
<L>&yogh;wite &yogh;e wel &thorn;e fremde and sibbe,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;es ne may nou&yogh;t a mong us libbe,</L>
<L N="845">For he were wuy&thorn;e nov &thorn;er to<NOTE PLACE="foot">wuy&thorn;e <I>statt</I> wuyr&thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>On &thorn;e rode to beon i do,</L>
<L>For he schent alle ore lais.</L>
<L>&thorn;us he seide with his voiz.</L>
<L>I not &yogh;wat Deuel hine bi &yogh;at,
<PB REF="00000074.tif" N="30"></L>
<L N="850">Ne &yogh;wat heo was &thorn;at he sek,</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;e moder &thorn;at hine bar;</L>
<L>Ich wene he wole us alle fur fare.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> heold him &thorn;o ful stille</L>
<L>And liet hem segge al heore wille.</L>
<L N="855">Manie sike weren in &thorn;at stude</L>
<L>&thorn;at to is help hadden neode:</L>
<L>So &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;oru&yogh; is meoknesse</L>
<L>Heom halp and helde of heore sicknesse.</L>
<L>&thorn;are he made &thorn;e halte go,</L>
<L N="860">&thorn;e Doumbe to speke he dude al so,</L>
<L>&thorn;e blinde he dude to habbe heore si&yogh;ht.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;is he dude &thorn;oru&yogh; is mi&yogh;hte.</L>
<L>&thorn;e maistres weren in gret fere</L>
<L>For &thorn;e miracle &thorn;at huy seien &thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="865">Wel huy i seien and vnder stode</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist milde of mode</L>
<L>Mi&yogh;hte don al is wille</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e loude and eke stille.</L>
<L>&thorn;are aftur huy dradden &thorn;e more <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR></L>
<L N="870">For is signes and for is vertu.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam Jesus with o&thorn;ur children and cloumben in to a soler, so &thorn;at in heore strif &thorn;at on pulte &thorn;at o&thorn;ur adoun, &thorn;at is necke to brac a two.</HEAD>
<L>Swete <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> is seth&thorn;e i gon</L>
<L>To nazareth; wel guod won</L>
<L>He hath&thorn; i founde of is cunrede,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane Josep hine &thorn;udere gan lede,</L>
<L N="875">Josep was faire vnder fongue,</L>
<L>For he was i knowe wel hem amonge;<NOTE PLACE="foot">wel <I>klein &uuml;bergeschrieben</I>. e <I>in</I> amonge <I>ist nicht aus|geschrieben und ist vielleicht zu tilgen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Marie Jesum hire sone<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> mid <I>oder</I> with.</NOTE></L>
<L>To heom huy weren swi&thorn;e wel come.</L>
<L>Nou geth Jesus with heorte freo
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="31"></L>
<L N="880">With fale children in &thorn;at cite:</L>
<L>So &thorn;at &thorn;e children euerech on</L>
<L>Into a soler gonne gon.</L>
<L>&thorn;is children bi gonne for to striue,</L>
<L>And ech o&thorn;ur &thorn;rettnede swi&thorn;e;</L>
<L N="885">So longue huy striueden with wicke mod,</L>
<L>&thorn;at euerech o&thorn;ur vuele smot.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> him stille heold,</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at huy duden he bi heold,</L>
<L>&thorn;at o giv to an o&thorn;ur gan strike</L>
<L N="890">And &thorn;retnede hine wonderlike.</L>
<L>Ase huy striueden nou&yogh;t for &thorn;an,</L>
<L>&thorn;at on &thorn;at o&thorn;ur vuele nam,</L>
<L>With wra&thorn;&thorn;e and with wicke dede</L>
<L>He hine pulte in &thorn;at stede,</L>
<L N="895">So &thorn;at he ful doun of &thorn;e staire</L>
<L>And &thorn;ere a non ri&yogh;ht brac is sweire.</L>
<L>Jh&umacr;s crist no word ne sede,</L>
<L>Ake stille he stod and sai&yogh;h heore dede.</L>
<L>&thorn;is was in a satur day.</L>
<L N="900">&thorn;at &thorn;e giv &thorn;is ded lay,</L>
<L>&thorn;ar of a ros ful gret cri,</L>
<L>Of is freond &thorn;ere comen mani</L>
<L>And gradden and maden sori bere,</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo hine seie ded ligge &thorn;ere.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ist am Rande nebengeschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="905">&yogh;eot seiden &thorn;e schrewes &thorn;at stoden &thorn;ore,</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lasse and &thorn;e more,</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> hine hadde so i pult</L>
<L>Al with outen ani gult.</L>
<L>Josep a non huy gunne &thorn;rete,</L>
<L N="910">Alle &thorn;ulke of &thorn;at strete.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne spac Josep to Marie is wif:</L>
<L>&yogh;wat schulle we do, mi leue lif?</L>
<L>Echon on vs bi guynneth to crie</L>
<L>And wollez us do gret vilenie.
<PB REF="00000076.tif" N="32"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here spac Jesus to &thorn;is dede child and a rerde it fram de&thorn;e to liue, and &thorn;arof is frend glade weren.</HEAD>
<L N="915">&THORN;O spac Jesus sone aftur &thorn;an:</L>
<L>Ne doute &thorn;e nou&yogh;t, Josep guodeman,</L>
<L>For &thorn;oru&yogh; me nadde he non harm,</L>
<L>&thorn;is child &thorn;at lith here a slei&yogh;e &thorn;us warm;</L>
<L>With wrong &thorn;is folk blameth us,</L>
<L N="920">I segge soth ful i wis,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at bi fore heom alle iliche</L>
<L>It schal beon i proued aperteliche.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> made &thorn;ene dede a rise</L>
<L>And axede him in &thorn;usse wise:</L>
<L N="925">Nou seie &thorn;ou &thorn;e ri&yogh;hte soth&thorn;:</L>
<L>Ho &thorn;e pulte, ho made &thorn;e wroth&thorn;?</L>
<L>Pulte i &thorn;e ou&yogh;t, o&thorn;ur i ne dude?</L>
<L>Nai, seide he a non in &thorn;e stude,</L>
<L>Ake dude ilmo bi is name,</L>
<L N="930">He me pulte and dude me schame,</L>
<L>Neuere wrong ich him ne dude;</L>
<L>Wite it wel, Jesus, in &thorn;at stude:</L>
<L>He &thorn;at on &thorn;i name it leide,</L>
<L>Wite it wel god, &thorn;at he mis seide.</L>
<L N="935">&thorn;ou art so mi&yogh;hti and poustif,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou mi&yogh;ht &thorn;e dede &yogh;iue is lif,</L>
<L>And &thorn;araftur &yogh;iue bo&thorn;e loude and stille</L>
<L>To ech man al &thorn;at he wilnez;</L>
<L>Mi lif &thorn;ou me i &yogh;iue hast</L>
<L N="940">&thorn;at Ilmo bi nam me arst,</L>
<L>I &yogh;iue &thorn;ou me hast mi&yogh;htes bolde,</L>
<L>For &thorn;e icham up i holde.</L>
<L>&thorn;e kuinde of &thorn;at ilke grome</L>
<L>Makieth gret Joye and lei&yogh;eth i lome</L>
<L N="945">And &thorn;onkiez muche &thorn;at child <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR></L>
<L>&thorn;at on him dude so muche vertu.
<PB REF="00000077.tif" N="33"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here bad Marie ire sone <ABBR>ihu</ABBR> &thorn;at he eode to &thorn;e welle with a picher and brou&yogh;te it hire hom ful of watur, and he eode forth wel mildeliche.</HEAD>
<L>WIth&thorn; Josep Jesus is igo</L>
<L>In to &thorn;e toun of Jerico.</L>
<L>Muche folk huy founden hei&yogh;e and lowe</L>
<L N="950">&thorn;at swi&thorn;e wel heom wolde i knowe.</L>
<L>Of six &yogh;er elde was Jesus &thorn;o,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he &thorn;udere wolde go.</L>
<L>Gret miracle dude he bi eche contrei&yogh;e,</L>
<L>&yogh;ware of marie hadde gret Joye.</L>
<L N="955">Marie gan cleopie iesum &thorn;ere:</L>
<L>Com hider to me, mi sone deore!</L>
<L>Leoue sone, fain woldi with alle</L>
<L>Drinke &yogh;eonde of &thorn;ulke welle;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou tak a picher a go a non<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a statt</I> &amacr; <I>oder</I> and.</NOTE></L>
<L N="960">And of &thorn;at watur bring me hom!</L>
<L>Mi leue sone, hi&yogh;e &thorn;e swi&thorn;e,</L>
<L>Guode child, &thorn;ou com wel bliue!</L>
<L>To &thorn;e welle he geth&thorn; eorninde,</L>
<L>In is hond is picher berinde;</L>
<L N="965">He it fullez a non ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>And hamward eornez with heorte li&yogh;ht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam a giv and brac Jesues picher, and &thorn;o is picher was to broke, he gaderede &thorn;at &yogh;watur into is lappe and anon ri&yogh;ht bar it hom to is Moder.</HEAD>
<L>Ase Jesus was hamward goinde,</L>
<L>A felun giv him cam metinde;</L>
<L>To Jesum wordes kete he spac</L>
<L N="970">And is picher he al to brac.</L>
<L>&thorn;o Jesues picher was to broke,</L>
<L>And &thorn;e wicke giv a wei i lope:
<PB REF="00000078.tif" N="34"></L>
<L>&thorn;e scherdes liet &thorn;are ligge &thorn;at child Jesu</L>
<L>And up he gaderede with his vertu</L>
<L N="975">Al &thorn;at watur in &thorn;at stude</L>
<L>And in is lappe he it dude.</L>
<L>In &thorn;at time so Jesus wrou&yogh;te</L>
<L>&thorn;at on &thorn;e grounde a drope ne lefte.</L>
<L>Hamward a non he wente eorninde</L>
<L N="980">And &thorn;at watur so berinde;</L>
<L>He cometh to is Moder a non ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>And scheweth hire hou he was i di&yogh;ht.</L>
<L>His Moder &thorn;arof wondri gan</L>
<L>And gret Joye hadde and lou&yogh; smere a non.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD><MILESTONE N="17" UNIT="folio">Here Jesus bar ane fewe Otene in is hond and caste heom in a feld, and a nonri&yogh;ht &thorn;e feld was ful of faire otene, and &thorn;at folk hem repen and a wei heom beren.</HEAD>
<L N="985">HIt nas nou&yogh;t &thorn;are aftur long stounde,</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> ane fewe Otene founde,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ulke he caste in one felde,</L>
<L>&thorn;are nou&yogh;t ne grev er bote gras wilde;</L>
<L>And in a &yogh;wile sone aftur a non</L>
<L N="990">&thorn;e feld with Otene was al bi gon;</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e faire Otene &thorn;are were wexinde.</L>
<L>Jhesus ne made &thorn;arof no &yogh;elpingue.</L>
<L>&thorn;at folk wondrede muche in heore &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Hou &thorn;e Otene weren &thorn;udere i brou&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="995">&thorn;at ilke fol it gounne schere<NOTE PLACE="foot">fol <I>st.</I> folc, <I>wie</I> 710 chil <I>st.</I> child.</NOTE></L>
<L>And hom to heore houses it bere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here hadden giwes idon heore children in one Ouene, for <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> ne scholde heom nou&yogh;t finde to pleie with heom.</HEAD>
<L>SEth&thorn;e &thorn;are aftur him sulf is go<NOTE PLACE="foot">s <I>in</I> is <I>ist &uuml;ber|geschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>With oute fere to Jerico.
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="35"></L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> ful of guod espleit</L>
<L N="1000">To &thorn;e giwes hath &thorn;us i seid:</L>
<L>&yogh;ware &thorn;e children mi&yogh;hten be</L>
<L>&thorn;at weren of &thorn;at contre:</L>
<L>&thorn;at weren mine pleiing fere.</L>
<L>Huy gounne &thorn;us segge, heom to skere:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> scere <I>mit &uuml;berschriebenem</I> k, <I>ohne dass jedoch</I> c <I>aus|gestrichen ist.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="1005">We ne wusten nou&yogh;t &yogh;are gret stounde</L>
<L>Hou ne &yogh;ware huy mi&yogh;hten be founde;</L>
<L>And wite &thorn;ou it wel &thorn;are fore</L>
<L>Huy it schullen a bugge sore.</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e giwes more and lasse</L>
<L N="1010">Hadden heore children with oute misse</L>
<L>In heore Ouene i pult and i do,</L>
<L>For heo ne scholden be i sei&yogh;e no&yogh;wer go</L>
<L>With Jesu, ase huy i wonede were,</L>
<L>Forto plei&yogh;e here ne &thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="1015">Of him huy seiden euere &thorn;at worste</L>
<L>Ni&yogh;ht and day, ase huy dorste.</L>
<L>Jesus wuste heore foule wille &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>And &yogh;ware &thorn;e children i hudde were.</L>
<L>Nou&yogh;t for &thorn;an for loue he heom bad</L>
<L N="1020">&thorn;at he were to heom i lad,</L>
<L>And seide he wolde gon in wei&yogh;e</L>
<L>Loueliche and with heom plei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes bigonne &thorn;o to swere</L>
<L>And seiden huy nusten &yogh;ware huy were.</L>
<L N="1025">Jesus him sulue is i gon</L>
<L>To &thorn;at Ouene him sulf al on.</L>
<L>Ate giwes he axede skeot</L>
<L>&yogh;wat were in &thorn;at ouene i put.</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes gounne to make sware</L>
<L N="1030">And seiden &thorn;at alle swyn it ware.</L>
<L>Jhesus to hem seide &thorn;o:</L>
<L>And hit swin beon euere mo.</L>
<L>And ech of heom also swi&thorn;e
<PB REF="00000080.tif" N="36"></L>
<L>Swyn bi cam &thorn;at ilke si&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="1035">And ase swyn huy eten mete.</L>
<L>&thorn;us was <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> on heom a wreke.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here founden &thorn;e giwes heore children swyn &thorn;oru&yogh;h Jesu cristess mi&yogh;te, and &thorn;e giwes ful sorie weren for &thorn;at cas and for o&thorn;ur mo and playneden heom muche of is dedes.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist was i gon,</L>
<L>vndut was &thorn;e Ouene a non,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ulke &thorn;at weren i pult &thorn;er in</L>
<L N="1040">Comen out for so&thorn;e swyn.</L>
<L>Alle huy heolden heom for dede</L>
<L>And i schende for heore mede;</L>
<L>And euereft seth&thorn;e for to &thorn;is</L>
<L>&thorn;e Gyv for bro&thorn;ur heold i wis</L>
<L N="1045">Euerech swyn in heore manere;</L>
<L>&thorn;is was a miracle clere;</L>
<L>Ne neuer eft fram &thorn;at to &thorn;is</L>
<L>Gywes ne eten of swynes flechs,</L>
<L>Ne neuere huy nelleth rau ne i zode,</L>
<L N="1050">For heore lawe it haueth for bode.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here lupten &thorn;e giwes to hore schendnesse, for huy breken heore neckene, and <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> suffrede wel heore folie; bote aftur &thorn;an he a rerde heom wel mildeliche.</HEAD>
<L>EFt sone &yogh;eot <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> gan go</L>
<L>With oute leue to Jerico</L>
<L>And hath i met &yogh;uyt eft sone</L>
<L>Fale children &thorn;at to him come;</L>
<L N="1055">And he bi heold with guode hele</L>
<L>&thorn;e children, for &thorn;are comen feole.</L>
<L>And &thorn;o he was &thorn;annes wendinde,</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e children him come siwinde.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e sonne bem he eode with liste<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e <I>im Ms. doppelt.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="1060"><ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist &thorn;at alle &thorn;ing wuste.
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="37"></L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> is curtel a non of dude,</L>
<L>And so duden alle in &thorn;at stude.</L>
<L>&thorn;o is curtel i don of was,</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> hine hangede ful of solas</L>
<L N="1065">On &thorn;e sonne bem and &thorn;ar on sat,</L>
<L>&thorn;at euerech one huy i seien &thorn;at.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> sone aftur a doun gan li&yogh;te;</L>
<L>Alle huy hine bi heolden ful faste with si&yogh;te</L>
<L>And wenden wel ri&yogh;ht so forto done</L>
<L N="1070">And gonne to fondi euerech one,</L>
<L>Bote on, ake &thorn;e o&thorn;ure alle at ene</L>
<L>Wolden sitte on &thorn;e sonne beme.</L>
<L>Ac to rakele &thorn;o &thorn;ei were,</L>
<L>&yogh;ware fore &thorn;o huy fullen &thorn;ere;</L>
<L N="1075">On and o&thorn;ur a non up lep</L>
<L>To &thorn;e sonne bem with cours gret;</L>
<L>Ake vuel hap heom cam to:</L>
<L>Alle huy breken heore neckes a two,</L>
<L>Bote on, ake he with oute duelle</L>
<L N="1080">&thorn;is dede gan wide telle</L>
<L>To al folk ase he gan go,</L>
<L>And gret cri a rerde &thorn;o.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here comen &thorn;e Giwes and &thorn;retneden Josepe wonderliche, and Josep was in gret a nuy and swi&thorn;e sori in is heorte.</HEAD>
<L><B>&THORN;E</B> grete Maistres of &thorn;at cite</L>
<L>Sone aftur Josep senden heo</L>
<L N="1085">And of heore sones tolden al heore &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Hou huy weren to de&thorn;e i brou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Josep was &thorn;o ful sori Man</L>
<L>And answerie heom &thorn;us bi gan:</L>
<L>Me of &thorn;inchez &thorn;oru&yogh;h alle &thorn;ingue</L>
<L N="1090">Of Jesues conteygningue;</L>
<L>Bote i ne may in none wise</L>
<L>Of is dedes hine Justise.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne wolde he schewie &thorn;er</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> crist was to feor:</L>
<L N="1095">Bote, maistres, wite &yogh;e alle &thorn;is:
<PB REF="00000082.tif" N="38"></L>
<L>&thorn;ei he beo &yogh;ong, he is ful wis;</L>
<L>Ac &yogh;if ich were in &thorn;at wille</L>
<L>&thorn;at ich seide ou&yogh;t him for to grulle,</L>
<L>He wolde cuy&thorn;e on me is mi&yogh;ht,</L>
<L N="1100">And &thorn;at were ful guod ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>I not nou&yogh;ware so wis child non.</L>
<L>And he him hadde ou&yogh;t misdon,</L>
<L>&thorn;at him ne scholde repenti,</L>
<L>&yogh;if he him wolde ou&yogh;t harmi.</L>
<L N="1105">&thorn;o answereden &thorn;e giwes proude</L>
<L>With kete wordes and and with loude:</L>
<L>&yogh;wat wolle &yogh;e with dedes bolde</L>
<L>A &yogh;eines us bataile holde?</L>
<L>Josep: Nai, ac ichulle fonde</L>
<L N="1110">Him to bidde with meokenesse</L>
<L>&thorn;at he lete &thorn;is wickedenesse,</L>
<L>And so schal al so Marie,</L>
<L>&thorn;at is his Moder leof and dri&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes: Nou, Josep, wel wite &thorn;ou:</L>
<L N="1115">Bote &thorn;ou remue heonnes <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>,</L>
<L>We schulle a wei driue eou i fere,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e ne schullen non more come here.</L>
<L>Josep: I ne rechche &yogh;wodere ich go,</L>
<L>For ich &thorn;olie muche wo,</L>
<L N="1120">And wite &yogh;e it wel me reweth i wis</L>
<L>For Marie, vuele an aise heo is.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here a li&yogh;hte <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> of &thorn;e sonne bem and a rerde priueliche fram de&thorn;e to liue &thorn;ulke &thorn;at &thorn;are weren dede, and huy &thorn;onkeden <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> swi&thorn;e muche in heore manere.</HEAD>
<L>JEsu crist ful of mi&yogh;te</L>
<L>A doun of &thorn;e sonne bem a li&yogh;te,</L>
<L>Forth he &yogh;eode priue and stille,</L>
<L N="1125">Ne schewede he no man is wille:</L>
<L>&thorn;e dede he a rerde euerechon,</L>
<L>And sone &thorn;annes he gan gon.</L>
<L>Alle huy &thorn;onkeden hine &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>For he so faire heom gan a rere.
<PB REF="00000083.tif" N="39"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here drof Josep a wei <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> and seide &thorn;at he ne scholde none lenguore duelle with him, for he was so muche i blamed for is dedes.</HEAD>
<L N="1130">JEsus in &thorn;e age of seue &yogh;er eode,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he a rerde &thorn;is children dede.</L>
<L>Hom he geth seth&thorn;e with guod espleit;</L>
<L>And Josep hath &thorn;us to <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> i seid:</L>
<L>I ne mot soffri in none manere</L>
<L N="1135">&thorn;at &thorn;ou beo lenguore with me here;</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;ine dedes nou&yogh;t I ne de sire,</L>
<L>For huy me fallez ofte to Ire;</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;e Maistres of Mi pere</L>
<L>And al &thorn;e contre a boute here</L>
<L N="1140">And muche folk al so of mi sibrede</L>
<L>Me habbuth i charget and i bede<MILESTONE N="18" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou beo fram me i bounde</L>
<L>And non more here i founde,</L>
<L>And, bote &thorn;ou beo, for so&thorn;e i sei&yogh;e</L>
<L N="1145">&thorn;at &thorn;ou beo i driue out of &thorn;is contreie;</L>
<L>For &thorn;ou art folliche of seuen &yogh;er elde</L>
<L>And li&yogh;ht and mi&yogh;ht &thorn;i sulf wel welde;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou nere neuere wrong doinde</L>
<L>Ne to noman vuel spekinde:</L>
<L N="1150">&thorn;ou mi&yogh;ht with &thorn;e lasse care</L>
<L>Libben &yogh;ware &thorn;ou euere fare. &mdash;</L>
<L>Swuch am i nou&thorn;e ase ich am;</L>
<L>Ne beo for me in wrath&thorn;e non,</L>
<L>For i schal with mi dede</L>
<L N="1155">Socur finde in som stede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> to a deistare and seide &thorn;at he wolde fain bi leue with him. &thorn;e deistare him grauntede and bad him do alle &thorn;e clo&thorn;us in &thorn;reo Caudrones, and &thorn;e deistare eode forth fram him and liet <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> i wor&thorn;e.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus nolde non lengore more,</L>
<L>For he was li&yogh;t and guod of lore.
<PB REF="00000084.tif" N="40"></L>
<L>He cam to a diestare</L>
<L>And seide he cou&thorn;e of his mestere.</L>
<L N="1160">&thorn;is diestere with oute blame</L>
<L>Of &thorn;is childe hadde game</L>
<L>For is semblaunt and for is dede.</L>
<L>Cum nou forth! to him he seide,</L>
<L>Nov seie &thorn;ou me with oute misse:</L>
<L N="1165">Hast &thorn;ou &thorn;are to guode wilnesse</L>
<L>A ri&yogh;ht for to serue me? &mdash;</L>
<L>&yogh;e, for so&thorn;e i sei&yogh;e &thorn;e. &mdash;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou art &yogh;oung, ful wel i se;</L>
<L>Ake &yogh;if ich mi cloth&thorn; take &thorn;e,</L>
<L N="1170">Hov wolt &thorn;ou do? seie me &thorn;i &thorn;ou&yogh;t! &mdash;</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e wel, sire, ne care &thorn;ou nou&yogh;t! &mdash;</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou wel dost, &thorn;e tit also.</L>
<L>Nov worth i sene hou &thorn;ou wolt do.</L>
<L>&thorn;ou schalt &thorn;eos &thorn;reo clo&thorn;es do a non</L>
<L N="1175">Ech of heom in o Caudroun,</L>
<L>For ich &thorn;e wolle segge soth&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;is on schal beo fair blu cloth,</L>
<L>&thorn;is o&thorn;ur grene, onder stond &thorn;is! &mdash;</L>
<L>&yogh;e, sire, ful wel i wis. &mdash;</L>
<L N="1180">&thorn;e &thorn;ridde mot beo scarlat i wrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>For ich it habbe deore a bou&yogh;t;</L>
<L>Do nou wel, for ichulle go</L>
<L>And al bi time come &thorn;e to;</L>
<L>And ope &thorn;i lijf ich &thorn;e defende</L>
<L N="1185">&thorn;at non ne come o&thorn;ur hende</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e clo&thorn;es &thorn;at beoth&thorn; in &thorn;i bailie,</L>
<L>For it were gret folie;</L>
<L>I schend it were al to nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Bote ech beo in is caudrone i brou&yogh;t;</L>
<L N="1190">And euerech bi him sulue mot beo ido.</L>
<L>Loke, mi sone, &thorn;at hit beo so.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> answerede: &thorn;art &thorn;ou nou&yogh;t care;</L>
<L>Ful sikerliche &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t fare;</L>
<L>Ichulle do wel, &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt i seo</L>
<L N="1195">&yogh;wane &thorn;ou comest hom a &yogh;e.
<PB REF="00000085.tif" N="41"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here eode &thorn;e diestere out, and ore louerd dude alle &thorn;reo &thorn;e clo&thorn;us into one caudrone a &yogh;en &thorn;e diestare heste, and &thorn;o he hadde so ido, <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> eode a wei stilleliche anon.</HEAD>
<L>&YOGH;Wan &thorn;e maister was i go,</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> tok alle &thorn;e clo&thorn;es &thorn;o</L>
<L>And hastifliche into one caudrone</L>
<L>He dude heom alle swi&thorn;e sone.</L>
<L N="1200">He was ful siker of his mestere</L>
<L>Jesus, &thorn;o he bi cam diestere,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he wolde wurche stille</L>
<L>Algate bi is owene wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;eos &thorn;reo clo&thorn;es, ase ich er seide,</L>
<L N="1205">In o caudron to gadere he leide</L>
<L>And seth heom &thorn;ar inne verreiement.</L>
<L>An o&thorn;ur hadde heom so ful sone i schend.</L>
<L>&thorn;o he hadde so i do,</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> fram &thorn;annes is i go;</L>
<L N="1210">And &thorn;e Maister him gan hom schake</L>
<L>&thorn;at him hadde &thorn;at cloth&thorn; i take.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam &thorn;e distere and wende wel to habbe i lore his clo&thorn;es &thorn;at he bi tok <ABBR>ihm</ABBR>. Ake he heom fond wel a grei&thorn;ede alle in one caudrone.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O &thorn;is maister was i come hom</L>
<L>And hadde i failled of is grom,</L>
<L>He was &thorn;o ful wel i war</L>
<L N="1215">&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> nolde come eft sone &thorn;ar.</L>
<L>He gan swiftliche anon forth teo,</L>
<L>For to sechen is clo&thorn;es &thorn;reo.</L>
<L>&thorn;o bi cam he ful sori</L>
<L>And seide alas and maude cri.</L>
<L N="1220">A louerd! he seide, i schend ich am</L>
<L>&thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;at ilke luyte grom;</L>
<L>He me haueth bi traid al;</L>
<L>Euere in care libbe i schal;</L>
<L>Ich was gret fol &thorn;at wole soteli,</L>
<L N="1225">&yogh;wane ich scholde so hine preisi,
<PB REF="00000086.tif" N="42"></L>
<L>And &yogh;wan ich scholde him take in is wold,</L>
<L>Al busi beo he seue &yogh;er old,</L>
<L>And so is felun and doget</L>
<L>&thorn;at ilke luytel Jesuet,</L>
<L N="1230">And ich i leue wel &thorn;are fore</L>
<L>&thorn;at he habbe a wei i bore</L>
<L>Nou&thorn;e mine clo&thorn;us alle,</L>
<L>And inot &yogh;ware ich him finde schulle,</L>
<L>Ne &yogh;woderward he is at rau&yogh;ht,</L>
<L N="1235">For swi&thorn;e wide ich him habbe i sou&yogh;ht,</L>
<L>And &yogh;eot wolle, &yogh;if ich may,</L>
<L>Seche alle &thorn;e caudrones with oute delay;</L>
<L>&thorn;e tweie ich habbe clene i sou&yogh;ht,</L>
<L>Ake cloth &thorn;ar inne ne finde i nou&yogh;t;</L>
<L N="1240">To &thorn;e &thorn;ridde ich chulle binne</L>
<L>And loken, &yogh;if &thorn;er beo ani cloth inne;</L>
<L>For &yogh;if i may ou&yogh;t finde &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>It wole me vaille in sume manere.</L>
<L>To &thorn;at &thorn;ridde caudron he teu&yogh;</L>
<L N="1245">And fond cloth &thorn;are inne of wel guod blu&yogh;;</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he hauit a parceued &thorn;at,</L>
<L>Wel &thorn;e more he was glad;</L>
<L>Nou a swagez his dolur,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he find cloth of o&thorn;er colur</L>
<L N="1250">Grene of swi&thorn;e guod grei&thorn;ingue,</L>
<L>Ase he deuise at&thorn;e bi gynningue.</L>
<L>Guod is, he seide, ich do anon</L>
<L>Mine hond into &thorn;is caudron.</L>
<L>A cloth he fint of guod scarlat</L>
<L N="1255">Riche and guod and wel bi set.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he hauez i founde &thorn;e &thorn;reo</L>
<L>Faire, ase huy scholden beo,</L>
<L>Ofte he haueth god i &thorn;onked</L>
<L>&thorn;at him haueth so restored</L>
<L N="1260">Of &thorn;at cloth &thorn;at he tok <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> bi fore,</L>
<L>&yogh;wuch he wende were for lore,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he hom to is hous cam furst;</L>
<L>Ake nou&thorn;e ne hath he no &thorn;ing i mist.
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="43"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here bi lefde <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> longue fram Josep and Marie in one wildernesse and pleide wiht wilde beste, and Josep and Marie weren ful sorie for him and in gret care, laste he hadde i beo fur fare in &thorn;at wildernesse.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Mit der Schreibung</I> wiht <I>vgl</I>. forht <I>st.</I> forth 1622 <I>und</I> 1656, <I>und</I> witht 1320.</NOTE></HEAD>
<L>JEsus cam a &yogh;ein to is Moder deore,</L>
<L N="1265">&thorn;at him maude ful guod chere,</L>
<L>And also dude sire Josep,</L>
<L>Hine vnder feng with Joye gret;</L>
<L>Huy weren glade and of heorte mild,</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy hadden i founde heore child.</L>
<L N="1270">&thorn;o wenden huy forth&thorn; with oute lesing,</L>
<L>Ne mauden huy no long dwelling.</L>
<L>Of ei&yogh;hte &yogh;er was swete <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he scheoude &thorn;is vertu.</L>
<L>Ase huy wenden in heore wei&yogh;e,</L>
<L N="1275">Leouns fale huy habbuth i sei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Men, &thorn;at comen in pilegrimage,</L>
<L>Huy metten heom in grete rage</L>
<L>And a straungleden heom and also frete,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane huy in wei&yogh;e heom gonne i mete.</L>
<L N="1280">Josep of heom gret doute hadde,</L>
<L>For huy so foule &yogh;ollen and gradde.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne seide Jesu a non ri&yogh;ht:</L>
<L>Josep, ne dred &thorn;e no wi&yogh;ht!</L>
<L>Jesus al one to heom eode,</L>
<L N="1285">&thorn;is bestes heore wrot to him gonne beode</L>
<L>And ech of heom to him gan go</L>
<L>And in heore manere hereden him &thorn;o.</L>
<L>Of him huy hadden gret Joye and feste;</L>
<L>&thorn;at he was guod ful wel huy wuste.</L>
<L N="1290">Jesus &thorn;is child longue gan duelle</L>
<L>A mong &thorn;eos bestes al at is wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;o was Josep, for so&thorn;e i sei&yogh;e,</L>
<L>For &thorn;at child in gret a nuye.
<PB REF="00000088.tif" N="44"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here comen giwes to Josepe and to Marie and seide &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> was a strangled and i &yogh;ete with &thorn;e leouns for so&thorn;e.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;O Jesu dwelde longue &thorn;ore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ore, <I>ebenso im Reim</I> 429. 905.</NOTE></L>
<L N="1295">Josep it gan rewe sore:</L>
<L>Departi he wende sikerliche</L>
<L>Fram &thorn;e childe &thorn;at he louede muche.</L>
<L>Gret folk of &thorn;at contreie</L>
<L>&thorn;is child a mong &thorn;is bestes i sei&yogh;e;</L>
<L N="1300">Huy wenden &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> were to drawe,<MILESTONE N="19" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And to Josepe huy seiden &thorn;at sawe,</L>
<L>With &thorn;e liouns &thorn;are huy eoden,</L>
<L>For ofte si&thorn;es gret harm huy duden;</L>
<L>And &thorn;are fore Josep was in fere,</L>
<L N="1305">Laste &thorn;at child a straungled were.</L>
<L>Jesus wuste wel Josepes &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ake Josep nuste his ri&yogh;ht nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ne deuisen it al clerliche</L>
<L>&thorn;at he wolde schewen ri&yogh;ht openeliche.</L>
<L N="1310">Muche folk &thorn;are was i go,</L>
<L>&thorn;at hadden bi fore itold so</L>
<L>To Josep &thorn;at he was i spild</L>
<L>Jesus &thorn;at suete i blessede child,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at huy it sei&yogh;en for so&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="1315">Hov &thorn;e liones with wilde to&thorn;e</L>
<L>A stranglede hit puyr egreliche,</L>
<L>And seiden so aperteliche</L>
<L>&thorn;at it was for is sunne</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> was a strangled &thorn;anne,</L>
<L N="1320">And witht ri&yogh;hte &thorn;oleden destourbaunce</L>
<L>Josep for is wicke suffraunce.</L>
<L>&thorn;o huy hadden &thorn;us i seid</L>
<L>To Josepe with gret espleit,</L>
<L>Ase wel &thorn;e more ase &thorn;e lasse,</L>
<L N="1325">Josep nadde &thorn;ar of no blisse,
<PB REF="00000089.tif" N="45"></L>
<L>Ake he made sorie chere,</L>
<L>For he doutede heore manere.</L>
<L>&thorn;e giwes ne loueden <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> ne is moder,</L>
<L>Ne neuere ne duden fram &thorn;anes hider.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> to is moder and fond &thorn;e giwes &thorn;at &thorn;retneden Josep, and alle &yogh;eodem bi fore him and maden him gret Joye, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hiet &thorn;e liouns tuyrne a &yogh;en with oute ani harm for to done.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hinter</I> alle <I>fehlt</I> liouns; m <I>in</I> &yogh;eodem <I>st.</I> n <I>verschrie|ben</I>.</NOTE></HEAD>
<L N="1330">&THORN;Eo &yogh;wile &thorn;at folke was so in cheste</L>
<L>And with Josep striueden faste</L>
<L>And to him speken al &thorn;retninde,</L>
<L>Some of heom lokede bi hinde</L>
<L>And sei&yogh;en <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> faste cominde.</L>
<L N="1335">&thorn;o weren huy in grete mourningue,</L>
<L>For &thorn;e liouns manie raumpaunt</L>
<L>To <ABBR>ihm</ABBR> mauden so fair semblaunt.</L>
<L>&thorn;o huy seien <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> come,</L>
<L>Departi huy wolden alle and some,</L>
<L N="1340">For non of heom ne hadde no space</L>
<L>To par fourmi heore manace.</L>
<L>Jesus heom seide: stille stondeth so!</L>
<L>&thorn;o ne dorste neuer on for&thorn;ere go.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e liones he made a semblingue</L>
<L N="1345">bi fore heom with oute damagingue.</L>
<L>A &yogh;en &thorn;at folk: ouer wicke feolouns,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ist</I> he spac <I>zu</I> a&yogh;en &thorn;at folk <I>zu erg&auml;nzen, oder ist</I> a&yogh;en &thorn;at folk <I>zu</I> damagingue <I>zu zichen? Statt</I> ouer <I>ist m&ouml;glicherweise</I> euer <I>zu lesen, da ein nur schwach sichtbarer Strich an</I> o <I>dieses als</I> e <I>erscheinen lassen k&ouml;nnte</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>To muche i fulde of wicke resouns!</L>
<L>To muche &yogh;e conne of foule sarmouns.</L>
<L>Nou&thorn;e bi holdeth &thorn;eos liouns,</L>
<L N="1350">Hou heo beoth wisore &thorn;ane &yogh;e beo</L>
<L>In heore nature, &thorn;at mouwe &yogh;e i seo.</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e wel huy conne heore louerd iknowe</L>
<L>And maketh him Joye, ase huy wel oweth.
<PB REF="00000090.tif" N="46"></L>
<L>To &thorn;e liouns &thorn;o seide he:</L>
<L N="1355">Ich ov hote tuyrnez a &yogh;e!</L>
<L>Ne doth nou non harm more ne lasse</L>
<L>To &thorn;e folke in place &thorn;usse,</L>
<L>Are &thorn;at &yogh;e beon a &yogh;ein i wend</L>
<L>&thorn;udere, fram &yogh;wannes &yogh;e weren i sent.</L>
<L N="1360">Swi&thorn;e gret Joye huy habbeth i lad,</L>
<L>To &thorn;ulke heste huy beoth ful rad.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here hadde Josepes grom i coruen a treo schortere bi half a fote &thorn;ane it scholde beo tane solu&yogh;, and Josep wrathede him &thorn;ere fore.<NOTE PLACE="foot">tane solu&yogh; = to ane solu&yogh;; <I>vgl</I>. tamendement 111.</NOTE></HEAD>
<L N="1365">JOsep was a guod wisman,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he ou&yogh;ht on honde nam</L>
<L>&thorn;at scholde to harewe o&thorn;ur to plou&yogh;,</L>
<L>He cou&thorn;e it wurchen wel i nov&yogh;.</L>
<L>To Josep cam a bacheler</L>
<L N="1370">And seide he hadde to him mester.</L>
<L>A weork he gan him deuise</L>
<L>And bad him it maken bi a sise.</L>
<L>&thorn;o imaked was &thorn;e beuerage,</L>
<L>Josep cleope to him is page</L>
<L N="1375">And seide to him: herkne to me!</L>
<L>A bachiler haueth here i beo,</L>
<L>&thorn;at hath deuised of &thorn;is treo a &thorn;ing</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou most maken with oute lesing;</L>
<L>He hath deuised &thorn;us alri&yogh;ht,</L>
<L N="1380">&thorn;at &thorn;is treo mot beo &thorn;us i di&yogh;ht,</L>
<L>Faire bi hewe and sarre</L>
<L>At ei&thorn;ur ende euene and quarre,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at it beo euene of &thorn;is mesure;</L>
<L>Elles we leosez bo&thorn;e ore &yogh;wile and huyre.</L>
<L N="1385">&thorn;e grom him bi het swi&thorn;e wel i wis</L>
<L>To maken it aftur his deuis.</L>
<L>&thorn;o Josep was fram him i schake,</L>
<L>&thorn;e grom hauet to him i take
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="47"></L>
<L>His Ax &thorn;at guod was to his mester,</L>
<L>And bi gan for to wurchen &thorn;er.</L>
<L>He wende for to spede wel,</L>
<L>For he was li&yogh;ht and eke snel;</L>
<L N="1390">Ake he failede, ase us seith &thorn;e bok,</L>
<L>At &thorn;e leste more &thorn;ane a fot,</L>
<L>&thorn;at bi so muche it was schortore</L>
<L>&thorn;ane Josep it hadde deuised erore.</L>
<L>&thorn;o Josep it hadde vnder &thorn;ou&yogh;t</L>
<L N="1395">&thorn;at &thorn;et treo was mis wrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>He wrath&thorn;ede him sone in is &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>For he it ne mi&yogh;hte a mendi nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>And bi gan to chide wunderliche</L>
<L>With is grom certeinliche</L>
<L N="1400">And corsede him swy&thorn;e lodliche.</L>
<L>&thorn;o seide <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> wel mildeliche:</L>
<L>Josep, no &thorn;ing ne wrath&thorn;e &thorn;e!</L>
<L>Swy&thorn;e wel it schal a mended beo;</L>
<L>Josep, hold &thorn;ou &thorn;i pays nou&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1405">And ne lat no swuch word out of &thorn;i mou&thorn;e!</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here heold <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> &thorn;at on ende of &thorn;at treo and Josep &thorn;at o&thorn;ur, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> drou&yogh; &thorn;at on ende &thorn;at it was long i nou&yogh;h of mesure.</HEAD>
<L>JOsep him heold &thorn;o ful stille in &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ne dorste he is grom blami nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>And &yogh;if he wolde, i segge it eov,</L>
<L>Wrath&thorn;i him wolde &thorn;are fore Jesu.</L>
<L N="1410">Jesus louede Josepe a ri&yogh;ht,</L>
<L>And Josep <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> bi daye and ni&yogh;ht.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> seide to Josepe: cum ner,</L>
<L>For ichulle beo at &thorn;ulke ende &thorn;er,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms. urspr&uuml;nglich</I> at &thorn;at, &thorn;ulke <I>ist &uuml;bergeschrieben und</I> &thorn;at <I>getilgt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;usse ende here &thorn;ou most abide,</L>
<L N="1415">&thorn;at &thorn;ou ne mowe on nei&thorn;er side!</L>
<L>Hold nou faste &thorn;at i tok &thorn;e,
<PB REF="00000092.tif" N="48"></L>
<L>And drau&yogh;h wel &yogh;wane ich teo!</L>
<L>Go do nou&thorn;e ase ich do schal,</L>
<L>With outen ani a &yogh;en stal.</L>
<L N="1420">So faste huy habbez i drawe bo&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&thorn;at it is euene for ri&yogh;hte so&thorn;e</L>
<L>And i wrou&yogh;ht wel with &thorn;e beste,</L>
<L>Ase it was deuised ereste.</L>
<L>Josep swi&thorn;e glad was &thorn;o</L>
<L N="1425">&thorn;at euene weren &thorn;e endes two.</L>
<L>Sone &thorn;are aftur &thorn;e bachiler cam</L>
<L>And wolde is weork habben hom.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane he haueth &thorn;at weork bi holde,</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e gret pris &thorn;arof he tolde;</L>
<L N="1430">To Josepe he maude is gre</L>
<L>With guode wille, and so au&yogh;hte he.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here smot &thorn;e Maister <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> ope &thorn;e heued with ane rodde, and <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> wax wroth and spac grete wordes to him, and he ful a doun ded al so sone.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus was &yogh;ut &thorn;are aftur i bede,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he sum&yogh;wat on boke leornede</L>
<L>At a maister of &thorn;at contreie,</L>
<L N="1435">&thorn;at longue non swuch &thorn;ar nas i sei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>So &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> grauntede heom</L>
<L>&thorn;at in to scole &thorn;o he cam.</L>
<L>On a bok he bi heold,</L>
<L>And a Maister kete and beld</L>
<L N="1440">Axede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> and bad him rede</L>
<L>And telle a non &yogh;wat Alef seide,</L>
<L>&thorn;e strenc&thorn;e, and &yogh;wat it is to telle.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> heold him &thorn;o wel stille,</L>
<L>Ake <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> on him is ei&yogh;ene leide</L>
<L N="1445">And faire and sweteliche to him seide:</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou me seist &yogh;wat beth is,</L>
<L>Of Alef i &thorn;e wolle segge i wis.</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;e Maister was i wrath&thorn;ed</L>
<L>And hath&thorn; <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> i &thorn;retned.
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="49"></L>
<L N="1450">&yogh;eot eft he bi gan <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> a pose</L>
<L>And &thorn;us to him seide &thorn;is glose:</L>
<L>Nou sei&yogh;e me, &yogh;if &thorn;ou canst and darst,</L>
<L>&yogh;wi was Aleph i nemned furst</L>
<L>In Ebrv and destincte hit,</L>
<L N="1455">Ase wel ase &thorn;ou canst and mi&yogh;ht.</L>
<L>&yogh;eot seide <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR>, ase he seide er,</L>
<L>A non to &thorn;at grete maister:</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou wolt, with oute de lay</L>
<L>I schal Aleph vndo, &yogh;if i may;</L>
<L N="1460">Ake formest icholde, &yogh;if it so mai beo,</L>
<L>Alre erest i witene of &thorn;e,</L>
<L>&yogh;wat is beth, &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ou wite,</L>
<L>And &yogh;wat is in is strenc&thorn;e i write.</L>
<L>&thorn;o seide &thorn;e Maister &thorn;us, ate furst sau&yogh;t</L>
<L N="1465">He pede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> luttle: Ribaut,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> hepede <I>wol statt</I> he paide, <I>wie</I> sede <I>st.</I> saide.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;e hardiesse hou cam it &thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;us forto Aposi me?</L>
<L>&thorn;e Maister &thorn;o ne lengore ne a bod,</L>
<L>Ope &thorn;e heued <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> vuele he smot.</L>
<L N="1470">Jesus was wroth, wel mai man wite,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he him hadde so i smite.</L>
<L>&yogh;eot seide <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> to &thorn;e Maister: sanz faile,</L>
<L>&thorn;is &thorn;e schal luytel uaile,</L>
<L>&thorn;is &yogh;ift i schal &yogh;elde &thorn;e,</L>
<L N="1475">Ful sone a wreke i schal be;</L>
<L>Here nelle ich no lenger dwelle</L>
<L>Ne nou&yogh;t more with &thorn;e spelle.</L>
<L>&thorn;o feol &thorn;e maister a doun ded</L>
<L>Ri&yogh;ht &thorn;are bi fore heore allere fet;</L>
<L N="1480">&thorn;arof a ros a ful gret cri,</L>
<L>&thorn;o <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> &thorn;anene gan departi;</L>
<L>To Josep cam sone &thorn;e ty&thorn;ingue,</L>
<L>&thorn;at ne &thorn;ou&yogh;te him nou&yogh;ht fair with oute lesingue;</L>
<L>And &thorn;o gan Josep Marie calle</L>
<L N="1485">And al &thorn;is dede gan hire telle.
<PB REF="00000094.tif" N="50"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam a maister of &thorn;e lawe to Josepe and to Marie and seide &thorn;at <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> was swy&thorn;e wis.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus eode a &yogh;ein &yogh;uit eft sone</L>
<L>And into &thorn;e scole he is i come.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e Maistres i knowe he was</L>
<L>&thorn;e ra&thorn;er for &thorn;at erore cas.</L>
<L N="1490">&thorn;are Jh&umacr;s in is hond ane bok hadde,</L>
<L>Ake ful luytel &thorn;are on he radde;</L>
<L>His eiene he gan &thorn;ar on legge,</L>
<L>Ake &yogh;eot no word nolde he segge:</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e world and of &thorn;e lai</L>
<L N="1495">Muche it was &thorn;at he &thorn;are on sai;</L>
<L>Ake o&thorn;ur &thorn;ing he tok in speche</L>
<L>And of &thorn;e holie gost he gan to preche.</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;e Maister it vnder stod,</L>
<L>A non hc feol to <ABBR>Jhues</ABBR> fot</L>
<L N="1500">And seide to him with gret cri:</L>
<L>Jhesus, of me haue merci!</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;ilke maister for so&thorn;e &thorn;ere</L>
<L>To <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> was vmble and de bonere,</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e o&thorn;ure with grete wille</L>
<L N="1505">Merci him beden with oute duelle,</L>
<L>For swi&thorn;e wel huy it onder stode,</L>
<L>Al so wel in dede ase in mode,</L>
<L>&thorn;at hit verreie and trewe and sot&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> was.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at huy hadden i heord of <ABBR>Jhues</ABBR> mouth,</L>
<L N="1510">And &thorn;at he was god al weldinde,</L>
<L>For is sot&thorn;enesse and for is schewingue,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he tolde in is child hede</L>
<L>Ase in schewingue and in dede.</L>
<L>Fram &thorn;at tyme and so forth&thorn;ore</L>
<L N="1515">bo&thorn;e &thorn;e lasse and &thorn;e more</L>
<L>Heolden him for god almi&yogh;hti</L>
<L>A swi&thorn;e muchc hine gonne douti.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> A <I>st.</I> and <I>oder</I> an.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="51"></L>
<L>On of &thorn;e Maistres seth&thorn;e forth eode</L>
<L>And to Josep tolde and seide</L>
<L N="1520">Of <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> &thorn;at he prechede a non</L>
<L>To &thorn;e Maistres euerech on</L>
<L>&thorn;oru &thorn;e force of clergie,</L>
<L>And more schewede with maistrie,</L>
<L>And seth&thorn;e ech one with oute envie</L>
<L N="1525">To him merci gunne crie.</L>
<L>His wit, he seide, is of swuch doingue,</L>
<L>&thorn;at noman ne mi&yogh;hte make delayingue</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ing &thorn;at he wolde don,</L>
<L>For his pier nis in londe non,</L>
<L N="1530">&thorn;at schewe cou&thorn;e &thorn;oru&yogh;h ani vertu</L>
<L>&thorn;at to us seide &thorn;are Jesu;</L>
<L>For he purueide with is mi&yogh;hte</L>
<L>&thorn;at tuyrne schal to grete ri&yogh;hte;</L>
<L>He is god, i sei&yogh;e for &thorn;i;</L>
<L N="1535">For &thorn;at is nou icome &thorn;at &yogh;wilene seide daui</L>
<L>In &thorn;e saume &thorn;at men callez flumcn dei,</L>
<L>&thorn;at muche spak of him sikerli;</L>
<L>So is nou&thorn;e wel i schewed</L>
<L>And bi him sulue wel i preoued;</L>
<L N="1540">Josep, i seie &thorn;e &thorn;is &thorn;ing</L>
<L>With outen ani kunne lesing.</L>
<L>&thorn;o was Josep bli&thorn;e and glad</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at &thorn;e o&thorn;ur him hadde i seid.</L>
<L>&thorn;e Maister fram Josep wende &thorn;o,</L>
<L N="1545">And Josep hamward gan to go.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here was a riche Man ded &thorn;at hei&yogh;hte Josep; and &thorn;o seide <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> to Josepe is fader &thorn;at he eode forto arere &thorn;ane riche Man, for he bar is name.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus and Josep and Marie also</L>
<L>Sone aftur &thorn;is huy gounne go</L>
<L>Into an o&thorn;ur londe,</L>
<L>Capharnaum hiet, ich vnder stonde.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at <I>ist mit Absicht ausgelassen, wie das Relativ im Altenglischen auch sonst im Nominativ ausgelassen wird.</I> [note added from Berichtigungen, p. XLIV; originally read: <I>fehlt</I> hit <I>vor</I> hiet, <I>oder</I> &thorn;at <I>im Anfange</I>.]</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000096.tif" N="52"></L>
<L N="1550">So &thorn;at Men wenden to seche</L>
<L>Fisicieins and eke leches,</L>
<L>For &thorn;are was sik a riche man,</L>
<L>His name ich eov telle can,</L>
<L>&thorn;at was wel i norisched</L>
<L N="1555">And swi&thorn;e softeliche i fed;</L>
<L>He was i cleoped Josep bi name,</L>
<L>And Man he was of grete fame,</L>
<L>Of alle he hadde loue and red;</L>
<L>Ake in &thorn;at tyme he was ded.</L>
<L N="1560">&thorn;are ase &thorn;ilke Josep ded was,</L>
<L>Gret deol men Mauden and seiden alas,</L>
<L>And for is guodnesse and his vertu,</L>
<L>For ech guod man him wel i knev.</L>
<L>Jesus is fader Josep gan calle,</L>
<L N="1565">&thorn;at he louede muche with alle.</L>
<L>Josep, he seide, hou goth it with &thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou nelt to &thorn;is dede Man teo,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane &thorn;ou hast i herd i nou&yogh;h</L>
<L>&thorn;at he bereth &thorn;e name &thorn;at dost &thorn;ou,</L>
<L N="1570">And him conforte with &thorn;i mi&yogh;hte?</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou so dudest, it were &thorn;i ri&yogh;hte.</L>
<L>Josep answerede, &thorn;at was loth to gabbe,</L>
<L>And seide: &yogh;wat may he nou&thorn;e of me habbe?</L>
<L>Josep, he seide, nou herkne me!</L>
<L N="1575">&thorn;at wiping cloth&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ou berst with &thorn;e</L>
<L>Tac and leie it opon &thorn;e dede!</L>
<L>And &thorn;anne &thorn;ou schalt &thorn;us him rede</L>
<L>And sei: to &thorn;e, Josep, i comen ich am</L>
<L>&thorn;oru&yogh; a child Men cleopiet <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR>,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at <I>ist mit Absicht ausgelassen, wie das Relativ im Altenglischen auch sonst im Nominativ ausgelassen wird.</I> [note added from Berichtigungen, p. XLIV; originally read: <I>fehlt</I> &thorn;at <I>vor</I> men.</NOTE></L>
<L N="1580">And &thorn;oru&yogh; him schalt &thorn;o habbe hele,</L>
<L>For he mai alle guodnesses dele.</L>
<L>Josep wende forth a non ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>And fond &thorn;e dede ligge i strei&yogh;ht;</L>
<L>Gret deol for him makeden &thorn;anne</L>
<L N="1585">Men and children and eke wommanne,
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="53"></L>
<L>For he was bi loued wel,</L>
<L>&thorn;are fore Men maden &thorn;e more deol;</L>
<L>Riche he was and i douted &thorn;e more,</L>
<L>For he was of hei&yogh;e kunne i bore.</L>
<L N="1590">&thorn;o Josep was comen in hastingue,</L>
<L>To him he seide a gretingue:</L>
<L>I comen ich am &thorn;oru Jesu,</L>
<L>&thorn;at ful is of muche uertu.</L>
<L>&thorn;ene dede he helde with &thorn;at cloth&thorn;,</L>
<L N="1595">And he a ros up with outen oth&thorn;.</L>
<L>He &thorn;onkede Josep with al is mi&yogh;hte</L>
<L>And him gan axi anon ri&yogh;te:</L>
<L>&yogh;wat is &thorn;ilke <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> &thorn;e wise</L>
<L>&thorn;at hath imad me fram de&thorn;e a rise,</L>
<L N="1600">Ase we mouwen alle i seo?</L>
<L>Seie me soth&thorn;, i prei&yogh;e &thorn;e!</L>
<L>Josep Answerede with oute delai:</L>
<L>Jesus is a god verray. &mdash;</L>
<L>Wel ich it i leue and &thorn;at is &thorn;ou&yogh;ht Min,</L>
<L N="1605">&thorn;are fore ichulle bi leue on him.</L>
<L>Gret Joye &thorn;are is and muche blisse</L>
<L>With Josepe and his sibnesse,</L>
<L>Huy habbez <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> &thorn;e more i loued</L>
<L>And &thorn;oru&yogh;h out al &thorn;e more honoured.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here eode Josep Jacobes sone into one lei&yogh;htone after wuyrtene; &thorn;are cam an Addre and envenimede &thorn;at child in &thorn;e honde; And &thorn;at child for grete anguische bi gan to crie, and ase he was ham ward, he mette <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR>, and he dude him guode vengaunce.</HEAD>
<L N="1610">INto Bedleem huy beoth i come</L>
<L>Josep and Marie with heore sone.</L>
<L>Of heore kunrade founden huy &thorn;are,</L>
<L>And for heom huy beth in &thorn;e lasse care,</L>
<L>&thorn;at heom habbez faire vnder fongue,</L>
<L N="1615">&thorn;o huy heom weren i come a mongue.</L>
<L>Jacob is Josep hiet calle
<PB REF="00000098.tif" N="54"></L>
<L>And bad him go swi&thorn;e with alle</L>
<L>A non ri&yogh;ht doun into &thorn;e lei&yogh;htone,</L>
<L>For to bringuen heom wuyrtone.</L>
<L N="1620">&thorn;is Josep was of &thorn;e sibnesse</L>
<L>Of <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> criste with oute misse.</L>
<L>He wende forht wel hasteli</L>
<L>&thorn;e wuyrtene forto gaderi.</L>
<L>In &thorn;at lei&yogh;htone, &thorn;are he was,</L>
<L N="1625">&thorn;are cam An Naddre out &thorn;e gras</L>
<L>And him envenimede in &thorn;e honde.</L>
<L>&thorn;is child gredinde hamward gan &yogh;ongue.</L>
<L>He haueth Jesum wel sone i met,</L>
<L>&thorn;at axede him sone with outen let:</L>
<L N="1630">&yogh;wi he made so gret cri;</L>
<L>And he answerede him ful hastifli</L>
<L>And seide: he was i hurt in is hond</L>
<L>With an Naddre &thorn;at him stong.</L>
<L>Bliue a&yogh;en &thorn;o seide Jesu:</L>
<L N="1635">To &thorn;e Naddre torne we nov!</L>
<L>&thorn;ou schalt beon a wreke, are we gon,</L>
<L>So &thorn;at harm ne tit &thorn;e non.</L>
<L>To &thorn;at Naddrc seide <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;o:</L>
<L>Cum out here and to berst a two!</L>
<L N="1640">&thorn;e Naddre to clef a non ri&yogh;ht</L>
<L>Euene a two &thorn;oru Jesues mi&yogh;ht.</L>
<L>Josep hadde gret Joye of &thorn;an,</L>
<L>And he eode him forth a non</L>
<L>To <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;at him gan calle,</L>
<L N="1645">&thorn;at handlede is hond &thorn;at was to swolle.</L>
<L>Jesus with inne is hond maude bre&thorn;ingue,</L>
<L>And &thorn;are after ne greuede it him no &thorn;ing.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam &thorn;at child hom with wuyrtene and seide hou an Naddre him hadde i stongue, and hou <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hine hadde i held.</HEAD>
<L>JOsep gadere &thorn;are wuyrtonc</L>
<L>And &thorn;are after he wente hom sone,</L>
<L N="1650">And ful sone he tolde is fader fore
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="55"></L>
<L>Hov an Naddre him hurte sore,</L>
<L>And hov Jesus helde him</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at ilke wicke venym.</L>
<L>Echone weren &thorn;arof bli&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1655">And &thorn;onkede <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> fale si&thorn;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here cam <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> and Josep and Marie to one feste, and heore kun maude gret Joye with heom.</HEAD>
<L>TO one feste forht huy eoden,</L>
<L>&thorn;are huy founden of heore kunrede</L>
<L>And o&thorn;ure mo with outen mis,</L>
<L>&thorn;at hadden of heom ful gret blis.</L>
<L N="1660">I sette huy weren a compas</L>
<L>To a bord &thorn;are inne was.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at <I>ist mit Absicht ausgelassen, wie das Relativ im Altenglischen auch sonst im Nominativ ausgelassen wird.</I> [note added from Berichtigungen, p. XLIV; originally read: <I>fehlt</I> &thorn;at <I>vor</I> &thorn;are.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;are was Jacob and Symeon,</L>
<L>Josep and Jude &thorn;udere com,</L>
<L>And two Maries of &thorn;at contre:</L>
<L N="1665">&thorn;at on was Marie cleophe,</L>
<L>&thorn;at o&thorn;ur also was i hote,</L>
<L>Josepes moder, of &thorn;at kunrede.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Diese Marie ist wohl die|selbe, welche in der Legende von s. Jacob (Ms. Ashmol. 43, fol. 63) Marie Salomee genannt wird, die Mutter von Jacobus, Joseph, Simon und Judas; die andere Marie ist die Mutter vom Evangelisten Johannes und Jacobus. Beide Marien werden in den Legenden sonst vielfach mit einander verwechselt.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Ech vnder fieng &thorn;at &thorn;udere cam</L>
<L>Wel faire <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR>, heore kunnes Man</L>
<L N="1670">Huy sei&yogh;en manie erore &thorn;ane &thorn;o</L>
<L>And is dedes i kneowen al so.</L>
<L>Ech louede ful muche <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR></L>
<L>And swi&thorn;e faire honoureden him.</L>
<L>His blessingue &thorn;are he &yogh;af &yogh;uyt</L>
<L N="1675">At&thorn;e bord and &thorn;anne he et,</L>
<L>Ase he was &thorn;are i sete;</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e gret plente &thorn;are was of mete</L>
<L>In &thorn;at hous, for ich ov lie nelle,</L>
<L>Ase &thorn;e bok us deth telle.
<PB REF="00000100.tif" N="56"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here eode Jhesus into &thorn;e giwene scole and desputede with heom, and Marie is Moder hine cleopede, and he cam to hire wel sone.</HEAD>
<L N="1680">JOsep and Marie bi leued beoth</L>
<L>In Jerusalem &thorn;at hi&yogh;e cite;</L>
<L>Aftur &thorn;at huy turneden a &yogh;e</L>
<L>And <ABBR>Jhm</ABBR> bi hinden heom bi lefte he.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e giwene scole <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> him tok,</L>
<L N="1685">And he gan loken on heore bok;</L>
<L>Al aday he desputede with heom</L>
<L>With questiones and heom ouercam.</L>
<L>&thorn;o was <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> of twelf &yogh;er,</L>
<L>&thorn;o he desputede with heom &thorn;er.</L>
<L N="1690">&thorn;reo dawes hire sone sou&yogh;te Mari,<NOTE PLACE="foot">dawas, <I>anscheinend im Ms. bereits in</I> dawes <I>corrigirt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And for him heo was ful sori;</L>
<L>&thorn;ene feor&thorn;e day heo fond <ABBR>ihm</ABBR> ate laste</L>
<L>Plaidinde a &yogh;en &thorn;e giwes faste,</L>
<L>And heo hine cleopede and hadde gret Joie,</L>
<L N="1695">And so wenten forth in heore weie.</L>
<L>Sone, we habbez &thorn;e i sou&yogh;t wide,</L>
<L>Josep and manie of &thorn;i kunrede,</L>
<L>And for &thorn;e we habbez i beo in sorinesse.</L>
<L>Jhesus answerede with meoknesse:</L>
<L N="1700">Ich habbe vnder nome, mi leoue moder,</L>
<L>To done &thorn;at me hiet mi fader;</L>
<L>&yogh;ware fore it moste nede beo so,</L>
<L>For he it me hiet forto do.</L>
<L>&thorn;o seide marie to Jesum:</L>
<L N="1705">Ine vnder stod nou&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;ou haddest to don.</L>
<L>Wel heo wuste &thorn;at Jesu</L>
<L>I fuld was of gret vertu.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here weren giwes i sete to &thorn;e mete, and win hem faillede, and Marie tolde hire sone fore priueliche.</HEAD>
<L>IN &thorn;e contre of Nazareth</L>
<L>So was &thorn;ere a gret a semble
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="57"></L>
<L N="1710">Of folk of &thorn;at ilke cite,</L>
<L>For &thorn;udere i bede weren heo:</L>
<L>&thorn;are was i wedded a wumman</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at Cite to a guod man.</L>
<L>At &thorn;ulke feste was gret pris</L>
<L N="1715">Of Archetriclin and of his.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Der Architriclin, der Oberaufseher der Tafel, erscheint auch sonst im Altenglischen als Eigenname ohne Artikel; vergl. Lydgate Poems p. 13:</I> Lyke to &thorn;e watyr of Archideclyne wiche be meracle were turned into wyne. &mdash;</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;o was Jesus &thorn;udere i come</L>
<L>And also of his desciples some;</L>
<L>&thorn;are was Marie with glade chere</L>
<L>For &thorn;et folk &thorn;at heo sai&yogh;h &thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="1720">To &thorn;e bord huy beoth i sete,</L>
<L>&thorn;e hexte furst and &thorn;e Maistres grete.</L>
<L>Glade at &thorn;ulke feste huy beth,</L>
<L>Muche folk of &thorn;at contrez,</L>
<L>Joye huy habbez i nov i lad,</L>
<L N="1725">And muche folk &thorn;are was bli&thorn;e &amp; glad.</L>
<L>Bote win bi gan to failli</L>
<L>To &thorn;at ilke compaygni.</L>
<L>&thorn;e Botiler ful sone cam</L>
<L>To Marie and conseil nam.</L>
<L N="1730">Marie &thorn;o with outen dwelle</L>
<L>Hire swete sone &thorn;is gan telle,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ere wyn i failled was<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> &thorn;ore, <I>anscheinend in</I> &thorn;ere <I>verbessert</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;are non more nas.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> answerede and seide sone:</L>
<L N="1735">Ich do al &thorn;at ich haue to done;</L>
<L>&thorn;is Maistres scholden &thorn;ar of &yogh;eme take</L>
<L>And nou&yogh;ht to me heore plainte make;</L>
<L>Bote ase a frend ich do schal,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane ich i seo tyme, i segge &thorn;e wel.</L>
<L N="1740">Marie gan &thorn;o &thorn;ene botiler calle</L>
<L>And heom hath i beden and i hoten alle</L>
<L>&thorn;at huy beon preste euerech one,</L>
<L>To don &thorn;at eov hat Jesus, mi sone.
<PB REF="00000102.tif" N="58"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>Here Jesus hiet bringue bi fore him fif pottes fulle of watur, and he &yogh;af &thorn;aron is blessingue, and hit bi cam guod win; and &thorn;e botiler &yogh;af &thorn;arof Archetriclin, and he dronk &thorn;arof, and him &thorn;ou&yogh;te neuere non betere wyn he ne dronk.</HEAD>
<L>JEsus &thorn;o with swete semblaunt</L>
<L N="1745">To him cleopede a seriaunt</L>
<L>And seide: go &thorn;ov a non and haste &thorn;e</L>
<L>And do bringuen here bi fore me</L>
<L>&thorn;e stenene More and &thorn;e lasse</L>
<L>I fulde of watur, i seie &thorn;e to wisse,</L>
<L N="1750">And &yogh;wane &thorn;ou hast i fuld &thorn;e stenes,</L>
<L>&thorn;ou nim a coppe fair and clene</L>
<L>And ful and sete bi fore Archetriclin! &mdash;</L>
<L>For it was &thorn;o ful guod wyn.</L>
<L>He dronk &thorn;arof, for it was so,</L>
<L N="1755">And him &thorn;ou&yogh;hte &thorn;at wyn betere &thorn;o,</L>
<L>&thorn;ane he hadde i dronken er</L>
<L>O&thorn;er i tasted elles &yogh;wer.</L>
<L>He cleopen &thorn;ane guode man<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> het <I>vor</I> cleopen.</NOTE></L>
<L>And to him seide &thorn;is resun:</L>
<L N="1760">I not hou i don &thorn;ov hast,</L>
<L>&yogh;wane &thorn;ou us &yogh;ifst nou&thorn;e worst,<NOTE PLACE="foot">nou&thorn;e, <I>wohl st.</I> nou &thorn;e, <I>scheint nicht richtig.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at betere wyn, &thorn;at &thorn;ou us &yogh;ifst,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e habbez for to nou&thorn;e i wust;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou scholdest at&thorn;e furste tyme</L>
<L N="1765">Habbe i &yogh;iuen us of &thorn;e beste wyne,</L>
<L>And so &thorn;ou haddest honour ido;</L>
<L>For gret loue i seie &thorn;e so. &mdash;</L>
<L>Graunt merci, sire, eouwer guode wille!</L>
<L>Ake &thorn;ei ich wolde nou&thorn;e telle,</L>
<L N="1770">I ne cou&thorn;e it nou&yogh;t descriue</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;e matere segge so bliue,</L>
<L>Hou &thorn;is wyn was hidere i brou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>For it was i dronken er euerech grot,
<PB REF="00000103.tif" N="59"></L>
<L>Wel huy habbez i seien &thorn;is cas,</L>
<L N="1775">Bote swi&thorn;e wel vnder &yogh;iten it was</L>
<L>&thorn;at <ABBR>Jhc</ABBR> hiet fulle of watur clene</L>
<L>Alle to gadere &thorn;e fif stenes,</L>
<L>And hiet &thorn;e botelers seth&thorn;e forth gon</L>
<L>And fulle &thorn;e koppene euerech on</L>
<L N="1780">And bere it bi fore Archetriclin;</L>
<L>And heo duden so &thorn;at guode wyn.</L>
<L>Drinkez nou, sire, and makiez eov bli&thorn;e,</L>
<L>For &thorn;anne it wole me gladie swi&thorn;e;</L>
<L>Ich abbe i dronken her of so muche</L>
<L N="1785">&thorn;at ich am ri&yogh;ht glad sikerliche;</L>
<L>So schulle sire and o&thorn;ere mo,</L>
<L>Are &thorn;at &yogh;e heonnes go.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> &yogh;e <I>vor</I> sire.</NOTE></L>
<L>Gret Joye and blisse maden heo,</L>
<L>Al &thorn;ut folk of &thorn;at contre;</L>
<L N="1790">&thorn;o huy hadden wel i dronke and i &yogh;ete,</L>
<L>Alle huy weren bli&thorn;e and glade,</L>
<L>And of &thorn;at Miracle &thorn;at &thorn;are was don</L>
<L>Huy hadden wonder euerech on.</L>
<L>Seth&thorn;e &thorn;annes huy beoth i wend</L>
<L N="1795">Bli&thorn;e and glade verreiement &mdash;</L>
<L>Bote some, huy flouwen for li&yogh;htnesse<MILESTONE N="22" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Der zum Vorhergehenden nicht stimmende Sinn der folgenden Verse l&auml;sst vermuthen, dass hier eine Reihe von Versen, vielleicht ein ganzes Blatt, ausgefallen ist. &mdash; Hinter</I></NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at huy i seien and for bri&yogh;htnesse.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane Jesu wende in anie route,</L>
<L>Inou&yogh;h he maude men of doute,</L>
<L N="1800">For non ne mi&yogh;hte bi holde with si&yogh;hte . . .<NOTE PLACE="foot">fehlt ein Vers.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>MArie and Josep eke</L>
<L>Weren wel ofte sorie and sike:</L>
<L>For Jesum ofte huy weren sori</L>
<L>And bi hatede of swi&thorn;e mani</L>
<L N="1805">And fale si&thorn;es in gret &thorn;retning;
<PB REF="00000104.tif" N="60"></L>
<L>Ake he heom halp &thorn;oru&yogh;h alle &thorn;ing;</L>
<L>And so bi heom <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> dude</L>
<L>&thorn;at alle heore freond &thorn;are fore were glade.</L>
<L>I blessed beo &thorn;at swete <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>,</L>
<L N="1810">&thorn;at here dude so muche vertu.</L>
<L>&thorn;oru&yogh;h is dedes he was i knowe wel</L>
<L>And so is &yogh;eot and euere beo schal.</L>
<L>&yogh;wane is moder ani &thorn;ing bad</L>
<L>To &thorn;e sone bli&thorn;e and glad,</L>
<L N="1815">&yogh;wat so it were, ase heo wolde</L>
<L>A non ri&yogh;ht for so&thorn;e it beo scholde.</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> louede is mode(r) ful wel and deore<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> mode <I>st.</I> moder.</NOTE></L>
<L>And hire honourede feor and nere.</L>
<L>&thorn;at hire louie, i blessed he beo,</L>
<L N="1820">And &thorn;at hire wel serui bi is pouste</L>
<L>And <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR>, hire swete sone,</L>
<L>&thorn;at for us wolde man bi come!</L>
<L>Mine leue nou&thorn;e take ichulle</L>
<L>Of eov alle with guode wille,</L>
<L N="1825">For i nelle eou schewen at &thorn;usse time</L>
<L>Non more in prose ne in rime.</L>
<L>Bote &yogh;e &thorn;at habbeth vnder stonde</L>
<L>Hov <ABBR>Jhus</ABBR> liuede child in londe,</L>
<L>Gret Joye &yogh;e mouwen habben nov</L>
<L N="1830">Of &thorn;at he dude &thorn;oru&yogh; is vertu.</L>
<L>Nov we schullen fremde and sibbe</L>
<L>With milde heorte to <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> bidde</L>
<L>&thorn;at he us &yogh;iue strenc&thorn;e and mi&yogh;hte,</L>
<L>Him to serui bi daye and ni&yogh;hte.</L>
<L N="1835">To is Moder seinte Marie</L>
<L>We schullen euerechone crie,</L>
<L>&thorn;at heo us graunti hire loue deore</L>
<L>bo&thorn;e in heouene and eke here.</L>
<L>Aungles and &thorn;e Apostles alle</L>
<L N="1840">With guode herte bidde we schulle,</L>
<L>And Martyrs and &thorn;e confessours,
<PB REF="00000105.tif" N="61"></L>
<L>&thorn;at huy beon ore socour.</L>
<L>Virgines and alle &thorn;at seruieth god</L>
<L>Bidde we with milde mod</L>
<L N="1845">&thorn;at huy beren so oure erende</L>
<L>To <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> criste al weldinde,</L>
<L>&thorn;at us &yogh;iue and grauntie pardoun<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> he <I>hinter</I> &thorn;at.</NOTE></L>
<L>And of ore sunnes remissioun,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at we mouwen at ore endeday</L>
<L N="1850">In to heuene comen an hei&yogh;h</L>
<L>And with him &thorn;are euere beo.</L>
<L>AmeN seggez par charite!</L>
<L>&thorn;e fader &thorn;at sit in trinite</L>
<L>Hit us graunti &thorn;at it so beo!</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit hic infantia <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> x'pi.</TRAILER>


</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="2" TYPE="part"><PB REF="00000106.tif">

<PB REF="00000107.tif">
<HEAD>II. Zur Geburt Jesu.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000108.tif">
<HEAD>A. Ashmol. 43.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Of Joie &amp; blisse is al my song, : kare to bileue,<MILESTONE N="208b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&amp; to herie him among : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> al our sorwe schal reue.</L>
<L>Icome he is &thorn;e suete dew, : to wan is al our hope,</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> kyng of alle kynges, : &thorn;e swete hony drope;</L>
<L N="5">Bicome he is oure bro&thorn;er; : war was he so longe?</L>
<L>He it is &amp; non o&thorn;er, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bo&yogh;te ous so stronge.</L>
<L>Oure bro&thorn;er we mowe him clupie wel, : so sei&thorn; he him sulf ilome.</L>
<L>So ne mi&yogh;te hi neuer adel : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bifore ous come.</L>
<L>He nas oure bro&thorn;er no&yogh;t, : ar he oure flesch nome,</L>
<L N="10">&thorn;er myde he ha&thorn; ous dere abo&yogh;t : to make ous isome.</L>
<L>Isome we nere bifore, : angelis &amp; oure kunde,</L>
<L>Ar swete <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> were ibore, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> to selde is in munde.</L>
<L>Ac nou he ha&thorn; oure kunde Inome, : &amp; oure bro&thorn;er is;</L>
<L>Oure kunde is wel heie i come : among o&thorn;er iwis.</L>
<L N="15">Vor he is al oure kunde hext : saue is godhede,</L>
<L>&amp; aboute is trone is next, : so noble is manhede!<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nach</I> trone <I>fehlt</I> man.</NOTE></L>
<L>Angel ne wor&thorn; no&yogh;t so hei, : for he nys oure bro&thorn;er no&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&amp; oure kunde is eke so hei, : he ha&thorn; ous dere abou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ne angeles he ne bo&yogh;te no&yogh;t; : we be&thorn; him wel ner;</L>
<L N="20">Wen he vs ha&thorn; so dere abo&yogh;t, : wel au&yogh;te men louye him her.<NOTE PLACE="foot">vs <I>ist im Ms. meist durch</I> v <I>mit dem Zeichen der Abk&uuml;rzung f&uuml;r</I> us <I>ausgedr&uuml;ckt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;e angel nys na&thorn;emo : bote as his messager;</L>
<L>Hou mi&yogh;te it &thorn;anne go : to beo is bro&thorn;er her?</L>
<L>&amp; In heuene hi scholle&thorn; also, : wen &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we be&thorn; &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Oure heste &amp; oure wille do, : as hi oure hinen were,</L>
<L N="25">To oure heste seruy ous : to fot &amp; to honde;</L>
<L>Oure owene we mowe holde ous, : as i<SUP>c</SUP> vnderstonde:<NOTE PLACE="foot">vnder stonde: <I>das ausschliesslich nach</I> d <I>gebrauchte Zeichen der Abk&uuml;rzung</I> <GAP> <I>ist &uuml;berall durch</I> er <I>wiedergegeben, obwohl es auch</I> ur <I>vertreten k&ouml;nnte</I>.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000110.tif" N="66"></L>
<L>Ne mowe we &thorn;enne glade beo : to habbe suche hyne?</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> so&thorn;e &yogh;e mowe her iseo, : as we ise&thorn; ate fyne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">suche: <I>Ms.</I> such; <I>der Strich &uuml;ber</I> h <I>ist stets durch</I> e <I>auf|gel&ouml;st</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we be&thorn; alle kunde hext, : wi&thorn;&thorn;oute god one,<MILESTONE N="209" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="30">&amp; in heuene also him next : among is angeles echone,</L>
<L>&amp; alle &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> nou&thorn;e late come, : se&thorn;&thorn;e our louerd ali&yogh;te</L>
<L>&amp; oure flesch ha&thorn; her Inome, : ihered beo is mi&yogh;te!</L>
<L>&thorn;ulke &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bifore ous come, : wen hi &thorn;en de&thorn; founde,</L>
<L>&thorn;enne hi were anon icast : In to helle gronde,</L>
<L N="35">Nere hi so holi ne so good, : &thorn;er nas vorbore non:</L>
<L>&thorn;erfore hem longede more : after our lord echon.</L>
<L>&thorn;e prophetes &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> were so gode : &amp; so holi alle,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> of oure lord vnderstode : wat it scholde bifalle,</L>
<L>Hi wusten &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wolde come, : ac hi nuste wanne;</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;e tyme hem &thorn;o&yogh;te longe Inou&yogh;, : ech vnche hem &thorn;o&yogh;te a sponne.</L>
<L>Hi gradden after him wel ofte : In here prophecie</L>
<L>&amp; In &thorn;e bokes &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi write, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he scholde hie.</L>
<L>God &yogh;eue, qua&thorn; on of hem, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heuene borste atwo,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he mi&yogh;te li&yogh;te adoun : to sauy ous so.</L>
<L N="45">Somdel hem longede &thorn;o, : wen hi nolde abide,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heuene cloue ofte atwo : to sauy ei&thorn;er side;</L>
<L>Ac he scholde al to berste : &amp; oure lord falle adoun.</L>
<L>Ac he hiede no&yogh;t so bliue, : he com softe al isoun;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> heiede, <I>mit unterpungirtem</I> e.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mi&yogh;te hi him habbe ihent : faste bi &thorn;e croune,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> halbe <I>statt</I> habbe; bb <I>ist im Ms. stets</I> lb <I>geschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="50">Hi him wolde narwe habbe iwent, : ac he hem huld &thorn;er doune.</L>
<L>Parde &yogh;ut ne com he no&yogh;t, : nere hem no so wo;</L>
<L>Hi &thorn;e grond of helle so&yogh;te, : ar he com hem to.</L>
<L>S. dauyd after his anuy : after him he gradde &thorn;us:<NOTE PLACE="foot">s <I>mit einem H&auml;kchen dar&uuml;ber</I> = seint <I>ist stets durch</I> s. <I>bezeichnet</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Louerd In heuene, to ous abowe : &amp; li&yogh;te to ous!</L>
<L N="55">Scewe ous of &thorn;in holi face, : &amp; we wor&thorn;e&thorn; hol anon.</L>
<L>Him longede ek after is face : &thorn;e holi symeon,</L>
<L>&amp; alle blisse him was bynome, : &amp; ofte gradde bifore:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nach</I> ofte <I>fehlt</I> e <I>oder</I> he.</NOTE></L>
<L>Louerd, wanne woltou come? : wenne woltou be ibore?</L>
<L>Wene &yogh;e i<SUP>c</SUP> mowe dure? : wene &yogh;e i<SUP>c</SUP> mowe ise?
<PB REF="00000112.tif" N="68"></L>
<L N="60">Here mone was deol to ihure, : ne gamede hem no gle;</L>
<L>Ac he ne mened hem no&yogh;t : a&yogh;en o&thorn;er bifore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hem <I>st.</I> him.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vor he nas no&yogh;t to de&thorn;e ibro&yogh;t, : ar god were ibore;</L>
<L>Ac he lyuede, vorte he him isei : &amp; in armes nom,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> iseie <I>u.</I> inome <I>mit unterpungirtem</I> e.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;o he acandelmasse dai : to &thorn;e temple com.</L>
<L N="65">Louerd, wel may ous beo : bet, &thorn;en hem mi&yogh;te &thorn;o,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> mi&yogh;te nowar fleo : ac to helle scholde go.</L>
<L>&thorn;er oure lord sede, : &thorn;o he was ibore,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;er <I>st.</I> &thorn;erfore.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we mi&yogh;te beo wel glad : ouer o&thorn;er &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> were bifore.</L>
<L>&thorn;e prophetes wilnede uorte se : &amp; mony kynges also,</L>
<L N="70">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we isee&thorn;, &yogh;if it mi&yogh;te be, : ac hi ne mi&yogh;te no&yogh;t do;</L>
<L>We mowe nou as it were : for no&yogh;t to heuene come,</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;e our lord ous ha&thorn; ibo&yogh;t : &amp; &thorn;e deueles power bynome;</L>
<L>Ac hi &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> such grace nadde, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> to fore ous come,</L>
<L>After oure lord hi gradde : In prophecie ilome;</L>
<L N="75">After him hi gradde : wi&thorn; grete wille &amp; longe,</L>
<L>No mendement hi ne seie : bote &thorn;e pine stronge.</L>
<L>So longe &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi weri were : &amp; lete al beo stille,</L>
<L>&amp; here aredinge forbere : &amp; turnde to godes wille,<NOTE PLACE="foot">aredinge, <I>st.</I> gredinge <I>verschrieben?</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Vor hi ne seie non o&thorn;er won : as ose seie&thorn; uor sore,</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="80">Vche of hem to reste drou&yogh; : &amp; ne speke of him nammore:</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> swete bern our kunde : bo&thorn;e of flesch &amp; felle.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nach</I> kunde <I>fehlt wol</I> nam.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of &thorn;e kunde of wan we come : somwat i<SUP>c</SUP> mot telle.<NOTE PLACE="foot">we come <I>f&auml;lschlich st.</I> he com.</NOTE></L>
<L>A good mon &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> me clupede isacar : was bi olde dawe</L>
<L>In bedlehem, &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> do&yogh;tren hadde two : In &thorn;e olde lawe:</L>
<L N="85">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> on was s. anne, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ber our leuedi marie,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> o&thorn;er elizabethes moder, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> het Ismarie;</L>
<L>Elisabhet bar of hire : s. Jon &thorn;e baptist,</L>
<L>&amp; marie, anne do&yogh;ter, : bar our lord ih&umacr; crist.</L>
<L>A good mon &thorn;er was In galilee, : me clepede ioachym,</L>
<L N="90">Scephurde he was &amp; holi mon, : gode grace was wi&thorn; him.<NOTE PLACE="foot">gode <I>st.</I> godes.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000114.tif" N="70"></L>
<L>&thorn;o he was of twenti &yogh;er, : s. anne he nom to wyue.</L>
<L>&thorn;er nas couple In ierlm : of so clene lyue.</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e hi doutede oure lord, : hi delde here good a&thorn;re</L>
<L>Vche &yogh;er, al &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi hadde, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ech man mi&yogh;te ise:</L>
<L N="95">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> o del hi &yogh;eue to &thorn;e temple, : to hem &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> seruede &thorn;er Inne,</L>
<L>As we &yogh;eue&thorn; oure te&thorn;inge : of &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we mowe awynne;</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> o&thorn;er del hi &yogh;eue to pouere men : &amp; weiueringe also;</L>
<L>Hem silue hi lyuede bi &thorn;e &thorn;ridde : godes seruise to do.</L>
<L>&thorn;er nere none men In ierlm : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> so muche good hadde,</L>
<L N="100">As ioachim &amp; his wif, : vor triwenesse &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi ladde.</L>
<L>Vor hose do&thorn; wel his te&thorn;inge : nou&thorn;e &amp; eke &thorn;o,</L>
<L>His good wole &thorn;e betere wexe : nou&thorn;e &amp; euer mo.</L>
<L>Joachim &amp; anne is wif : to gadere hor lif ladde</L>
<L>In clene spoushod twenti &yogh;er, : &amp; no child hi nadde.</L>
<L N="105">Aschamed &thorn;er of hi were sore, : for hem &thorn;o&yogh;te &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi were</L>
<L>Vor &yogh;ete of god to fore alle o&thorn;er, : vor no child hi ne bere.</L>
<L>Hi bihete god, &yogh;if &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wolde : eny child hem sende,<MILESTONE N="210" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To godes seruice oblege hi wolde : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> child wi&thorn;&thorn;outen ende.</L>
<L>Vche &yogh;er also ioachim : to &thorn;e temple wende</L>
<L N="110">&thorn;re si&thorn;e, to stable his biheste, : &yogh;if god him eny sende;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nach</I> eny <I>fehlt</I> child.</NOTE></L>
<L>&amp; offrede largeliche : of &thorn;ing &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he hadde,</L>
<L>ffor schame &amp; for sorynesse : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi no child nadde.</L>
<L>&thorn;o hi hadde twenti &yogh;er : hor lif ilad so,</L>
<L>Joachim offrede to &thorn;e temple, : as he was iwoned to do.</L>
<L N="115">&thorn;e prest &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;e temple wuste : pulte him abac anon</L>
<L>&amp; sede &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wer&thorn;i nas : a mong godemen to gon,</L>
<L>&amp; oure lord him scewede wel, : wen he ne &thorn;olede no&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nach</I> &amp; <I>fehlt</I> &thorn;at.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> eny child as of o&thorn;er men : were of him ibro&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Joachim was so sore of schamed : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wende out anon,</L>
<L N="120">ffor schame among o&thorn;er men : In &thorn;e temple he nolde gon.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; is scip he wende in to ano&thorn;er lond : wepinge wel sore.</L>
<L>He ne &thorn;o&yogh;te to &thorn;e temple come : ne to anne is wif nammore.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; scephurdes &thorn;er he was : In sorwe mon&thorn;es fiue,</L>
<L>He ne hurde no&yogh;t of is frendes : ne of anne is wyue.</L>
<L N="125">An angel com adoun to him : &amp; bad him be wel bli&thorn;e,
<PB REF="00000116.tif" N="72"></L>
<L>&amp; sede our lord him wolde sende : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wilnede ofte si&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> anne scholde a do&yogh;ter bere : &amp; of him be bi&yogh;ite,</L>
<L>To blisse of al &thorn;e world, : as &thorn;e prophetes hadde iwrite.</L>
<L>In toknynge he bad him go hom, : &yogh;if he ileue nolde,</L>
<L N="130">At &thorn;e guldene &yogh;ate his wif : he mete scholde.</L>
<L>Joachim ne leuede it no&yogh;t, : uor longe childles hi were,</L>
<L>Ac hamward he wende na&thorn;eles, : he ne dorste elles for fere.</L>
<L>Gret deol made his wif vor him, : no womman mi&yogh;te more.</L>
<L>As heo was in morninge adai : wepinge wel sore</L>
<L N="135">&amp; gan to wringe hire honde: : swete lord, heo sede,</L>
<L>Eche &thorn;ing &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> &yogh;euest Joie : &amp; eche &thorn;ing of blede,</L>
<L>Me one &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> makes Joie les, : Ine seo non o&thorn;er so;</L>
<L>Me wondre&thorn; &yogh;if i<SUP>c</SUP> dorste segge : wi &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> &thorn;enchest so do,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> &thorn;encheste <I>mit unterpungirtem</I> e.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wen &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> children hast me bynome, : &amp; me eke hast bynome</L>
<L N="140">Myn hosebonde &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> is my Joie, : Inot war he is bicome.</L>
<L>&thorn;o com &thorn;us an angel to hire; : doute &thorn;e no&yogh;t! he sede,</L>
<L>Icham &thorn;e angel &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> habbe ibore : bifore god &thorn;i godhede;</L>
<L>A dou&yogh;ter &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> schalt her bere : al bi godes rede,</L>
<L>Marie schal hire name beo, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> holi lif schal lede;</L>
<L N="145">Of hire schal wondri al &thorn;e world : &amp; &thorn;oru hire isaued beo;</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> child &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> schalt bityme bere : &amp; &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> so&thorn;e iseo;</L>
<L>A&yogh;en &thorn;in hosebonde &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> go; : to voluelle &thorn;i bone,</L>
<L>Ate guldene &yogh;ate &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> schalt him mete, : ne come &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> so sone.</L>
<L>Anne ne leuede no&yogh;t &thorn;is, : ac na&thorn;eles uor&thorn; heo wende</L>
<L N="150">Vorte Imete hire hosebonde, : as &thorn;e angel hire kende.</L>
<L>Joachim &amp; anne is wif : sone to gadere hem mette</L>
<L>Ate guldene &yogh;ate wi&thorn; grete Joie, : as &thorn;e angel hem sette.</L>
<L>Hi clupte &amp; custe wi&thorn; Joie Inou; : &thorn;e bet hi leuede &thorn;o,</L>
<L>Vor hope of &thorn;is holi child, : hamward hi gonne go.</L>
<L N="155">Anne se&thorn;&thorn;e wi&thorn; childe was, : &amp; se&thorn;&thorn;e wi&thorn; ri&yogh;te kunde</L>
<L>Bar &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> swete holi bern : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> euer wor&thorn; In munde,</L>
<L>Marie, &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ous ha&thorn; isaued : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> erore were ilore.</L>
<L>&thorn;e ei&yogh;te&thorn;e dai of septembre : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> swete child was ibore.
<PB REF="00000118.tif" N="74"></L>
<L>In ierlm heo was ibore : In hire fader house iwis</L>
<L N="160">Biside &thorn;e &yogh;ate of iosaphat, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> nou&thorn;e an abbei is</L>
<L>In honourance of s. anne : of blake nonnerie,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e stude &thorn;er heo was bore : &thorn;e swete maide marie.</L>
<L>Holi chirche nuste no&yogh;t : wuch dai heo was ibore,</L>
<L>Ar nou late &thorn;oru myracle : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> god dude &thorn;eruore.</L>
<L N="165">A good mon nou late eche &yogh;er : gret Joie in heuene isay</L>
<L>ffram &yogh;ere to &yogh;ere In septembre, : as falle&thorn; our leuedi day.</L>
<L>Our lord he bad ententifliche : sum tokene him sende &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Wi more Joie were In heuene &thorn;o : &thorn;en in o&thorn;er time were.</L>
<L>Angeles sede &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> for our leuedi : ibore was &thorn;ulke dai,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;at for <I>wol st.</I> for &thorn;at.</NOTE></L>
<L N="170">&amp; of hire burtime was al &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ioie : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he In heuene isai;</L>
<L>&amp; bad warny holi churche : &amp; men on er&thorn;e also</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hi made feste of &thorn;ulke dai, : as he sei in heuene do.</L>
<L>Hire burtime holi chirche : wuste In &thorn;isse manere.</L>
<L>Telle we of hire lif, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo ladde aner&thorn;e here!</L>
<L N="175">Anon as heo was &thorn;re &yogh;er old, : as it vel in &thorn;e lawe,</L>
<L>I offred heo was to &thorn;e temple, : as it vel bi olde dawe,</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo bileuede hire moder breste : &amp; ne sek namore.</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo to &thorn;e temple com, : me mi&yogh;te ise godes ore:</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;er were viftene de gres : bifore &thorn;e heie auter</L>
<L N="180">In &thorn;e honur of &thorn;e viftene saumes : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> be&thorn; In &thorn;e sauter;</L>
<L>&thorn;is maide clamb ech after o&thorn;er, : vorte heo com vp an hei,</L>
<L>As heo were of gret elde, : ne com nomon hire nei;</L>
<L>Heo ne lokede after no moder, : &thorn;o heo vpard stei.</L>
<L>Gret Joie hadde ech man : of hire &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hit isei.</L>
<L N="185">Chastete heo bihet, : &yogh;if godes wille it were.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; o&thorn;er maidens In &thorn;e temple : heo was iset to lere.</L>
<L>So vair heo was &amp; queynte : of witte &amp; of dede,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ech mon of such &yogh;ong &thorn;ing : wondrede &amp; were in drede.</L>
<L>Heo nas neuer iseie wro&thorn; : ne enes li&yogh;ynge gon</L>
<L N="190">Ne no misword enes segge, : bote euer heo was In on.<MILESTONE N="211" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Heo sewede &amp; span &amp; waf : bo&thorn;e wollone &amp; lynne,</L>
<L>Heo hadde lute erliche good, bote as heo mi&yogh;te wynne,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> erliche <I>st.</I> er&thorn;liche, <I>wie h&auml;ufig im Ms.</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Eche werkedai bi ri&yogh;te tyme : &thorn;en dai heo delde a &thorn;re:
<PB REF="00000120.tif" N="76"></L>
<L>Eche day vorte vnderne : In bedes heo wolde beo,</L>
<L N="195">ffram vnderne to mydouernon : to werke heo wolde sitte,</L>
<L>To spinne o&thorn;er to sewe, : heo was of gode witte;</L>
<L>In hire beden heo wolde &thorn;enne beo : vorte eue wel softe.</L>
<L>To hire angeles come al day : &amp; confortede hire wel ofte.</L>
<L>Wen heo hurde of sikemen, : sone to hem heo wende</L>
<L N="200">&amp; confortede &amp; helde hem : &thorn;oru grace &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> god hire sende.</L>
<L>In hire childhod hit was : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> i<SUP>c</SUP> &yogh;ou habbe itold.</L>
<L>ffor ech godnesse myd hire was : bo&thorn;e &yogh;ong &amp; old.</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo was fourtene &yogh;er old, : &thorn;e biscop of &thorn;e lawe</L>
<L>Het ech maide of &thorn;ulke elde : to hore contreie drawe,</L>
<L N="205">To take hosebondes as &thorn;e lawe was; : &thorn;e maidens were vawe</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ulke heste, bote marie : ne likede no&yogh;t &thorn;e sawe;</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo wi&thorn; o&thorn;er was ihote go : hosebonde to take,</L>
<L>Heo sede : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;e lawe wole, : nele i<SUP>c</SUP> no&yogh;t vorsake;</L>
<L>Mi fader &amp; my moder made biheste, : ar i<SUP>c</SUP> were bi&yogh;ute,</L>
<L N="210">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> i<SUP>c</SUP> scholde in godes seruise : my maidenhod wute;</L>
<L>I<SUP>c</SUP> my sulf, &thorn;o i<SUP>c</SUP> was child, : bihet our lord al one</L>
<L>To lede my lif in chastete : wi&thorn;&thorn;oute mannes mone;</L>
<L>&thorn;erfore i<SUP>c</SUP> &yogh;ou segge to so&thorn;e : al myne wille:</L>
<L>Nei man ne schal i<SUP>c</SUP> neuer come : my maidenhod to spille.</L>
<L N="215">&thorn;e biscop &amp; &thorn;e o&thorn;er maistres, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> In &thorn;e temple were,</L>
<L>Gret conseil nome of &thorn;is word : &amp; were in gret fere,</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;e lawe wolde &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> noman : a&yogh;en suche biheste scholde beo,</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;e lawe wolde &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> no womman : vn spoused me scholde iseo.</L>
<L>Gret conseil &thorn;er of hi nome : fram daie to dai in &thorn;e &yogh;ere</L>
<L N="220">In orisoun to bidde our lord, : som toknynge to sende hem &thorn;ere.</L>
<L>&thorn;o com a uois to hem &amp; sede: : &thorn;enche&thorn; in isaie!</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> maide ches hire spouse : &thorn;oru his prophecie.</L>
<L>Nou sede isaye : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;er scholde springe</L>
<L>A &yogh;erde of Jessees more : of dauid &thorn;e kynge,</L>
<L N="225">&amp; aflour scholde springe : of &thorn;ulke more also,</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;er vppe ali&yogh;te &thorn;e holi gost : &amp; come so &thorn;erto.</L>
<L>Her &thorn;oru &thorn;is men wuste : hou hi scholde on take.</L>
<L>Of dauies kunde he het eche man, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> was wi&thorn;&thorn;oute make
<PB REF="00000122.tif" N="78"></L>
<L>&amp; of elde to habbe wif, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ech of hem bere</L>
<L N="230">A &yogh;erde to &thorn;e auter, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> non vorbore nere;</L>
<L>&amp; wuche &yogh;erde bigonne to blowe : &amp; a coluere &thorn;er vppe ibro&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he tok maric to spouse, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> it nere bileued no&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&thorn;e biscop was &thorn;o glad Inou&yogh;, : he let crie &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Al &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> were of dauies kunde : a&yogh;erde to &thorn;e auter bere.</L>
<L N="235">&thorn;o hi were to &thorn;e auter icome, : ech hadde a &yogh;erde an honde.</L>
<L>&thorn;er was Josep an old mon, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bihynde alle gan stonde.</L>
<L>A&yogh;enes wille he &thorn;uder com, : he ne dorste elles vor fere;</L>
<L>His &yogh;erde he hudde, &thorn;o o&thorn;er men : hore to &thorn;e auter bere.</L>
<L>&thorn;er nas non &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> gan to blowe, : ac iosep hi vnder&yogh;ete</L>
<L N="240">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he hadde is &yogh;erde ihud; : hi gonne anon to &thorn;rete;</L>
<L>Hi made him bere uor&thorn; is &yogh;erd, : hit ne moste non o&thorn;er beo;</L>
<L>&thorn;o he to &thorn;e auter com, : me mi&yogh;te miracle iseo:</L>
<L>His &yogh;erde bigan to blowe anon, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ra&thorn;er was old &amp; bar,</L>
<L>Anoueward sat acoluere; : fair miracle was &thorn;ar:</L>
<L N="245">Vpe &thorn;e &yogh;erde longe heo sat, : &amp; se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> folc isei:</L>
<L>Heo flei in to al &thorn;e temple : &amp; se&thorn;&thorn;e in to heuene an hei.</L>
<L>&thorn;er nas non &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;is isei, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> sore adrad nas.</L>
<L>Ac Joseph &thorn;e oldeman : swi&thorn;e sori was;</L>
<L>&thorn;o me lokede him &thorn;e maide, : a schamed he was sore.</L>
<L N="250">Loke&thorn;, he sede, my feblesse : &amp; habbe&thorn; of me milce &amp; ore!</L>
<L>Nam i<SUP>c</SUP> old &amp; cke feble? : my mi&yogh;te is me bynome;</L>
<L>Heo is &yogh;ong &amp; sunne it is : make ous to gadere come.</L>
<L>Nym &yogh;eme, qua&thorn; &thorn;e biscop, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> &thorn;i sulf ne aspille,</L>
<L>As dude datan &amp; abiron, : vor hi were a&yogh;en godes wille.</L>
<L N="255">&thorn;o was Joseph sore adrad, : he ne dorste wi&thorn;segge namore</L>
<L>Vor drede of oure lordes heste; : he gan to sike sore.</L>
<L>Inele no&yogh;t god misdo; : wenne it mot be so nede,</L>
<L>Ichulle hire wedde, ac heo ne schal : for me hire maidenhod scede;</L>
<L>Ichulle hire wite as hire wardeyn, : o&thorn;er ne mai i<SUP>c</SUP> no&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="260">&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> my sone hire wedde after me, : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hire kunde be uor&thorn; ibro&yogh;t.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> kude <I>st.</I> kunde.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vor &thorn;e lawe was: wen man ne mi&yogh;te : bi&yogh;ute child bi is wyue,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> is nexte kun scholde : hire wedde after is lyue,</L>
<L>&amp; ech after o&thorn;er, vorte sun child : of &thorn;e blode come;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> sun <I>st.</I> sum.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hoso non wonne, vnwer&thorn;i was, : as it verde ilome.
<PB REF="00000124.tif" N="80"></L>
<L N="265">Joseph wedde in &thorn;is entente : &thorn;is clene maide &thorn;ere.<NOTE PLACE="foot">wedde <I>st.</I> weddede.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac for o&thorn;er &thorn;ing our lord nolde : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo iwedded nere:</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> is moder nere isclaundred : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo vnwedded wi&thorn; childe were,</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;e deuel it vnder&yogh;ete : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> a maide child bere;</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;er bi he wolde habbe iwust : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> it were godes sone,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Hinter</I> sone <I>ist von sp&auml;terer Hand</I> &thorn;ere, <I>hinter 271</I> sone <I>zugef&uuml;gt, offenbar um den irrth&uuml;mlich ver|missten Reim zu erg&auml;nzen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="270">&amp; habbe destourbed in alle &thorn;ing : of his passione;</L>
<L>&amp; god wolde ek, &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> is moder : were in eche god hod;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> goohod <I>st.</I> godhod.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of wymmen &thorn;re &thorn;er be&thorn; : &thorn;e hexte is maiden hod,</L>
<L>&thorn;e o&thorn;er hexte is widewehod, : spoushod &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is.<MILESTONE N="212" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Alle &thorn;re &thorn;e maide hadde : &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bar oure lord crist:</L>
<L N="275">Heo was maide widewe &amp; wif; : hoso nys non of &thorn;is &thorn;re,</L>
<L>Bote heo come to amendement, : non hope ne mai of hire be.</L>
<L>Ac na&thorn;eles &thorn;er wi&thorn;&thorn;oute : me mai ifynde some,</L>
<L>Ac, &yogh;if god wole, hi mowe amende, : ar hi to de&thorn;e come.<NOTE PLACE="end">Hier schliesst Ms. Ashmol. 43 ab; das Uebrige findet sich allein in Ms. Egerton 1993.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="[65]">
<HEAD>B. Egerton 1993.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Of ioie and blisse is now mi &thorn;ou&yogh;t, . care to bi leue,<MILESTONE N="27" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Vor te herien him among . &thorn;at al oure sor schal reue.</L>
<L>ffor icome he is &thorn;e swete &thorn;eng, . &thorn;e swete honi drope,</L>
<L>Jhs king of alle &thorn;ing, . to wham is al oure hope;</L>
<L N="5">I come he is oure swete bro&thorn;er; . whar was he so longe?</L>
<L>He it is and non o&thorn;er, . &thorn;at bou&yogh;te vs vrom pine stronge.</L>
<L>Oure bro&thorn;er we mowen him clepe, . so sei&thorn; him self ilome.</L>
<L>So ne mi&yogh;ten heo neuer adel . &thorn;at bi foren vs come.</L>
<L>Vor he nas here bro&thorn;er nou&yogh;t, . ar he oure vlessch nome,</L>
<L N="10">&thorn;er wi&thorn; he ha&thorn; vs dere abou&yogh;t . to maken vs i some.</L>
<L>I some nere hi nou&yogh;t to fore, . angles and oure kuinde,</L>
<L>Ar swete ihs were ibore, . &thorn;at seldene is in oure muinde.</L>
<L>Ac now he ha&thorn; oure vlesch inome, . and oure bro&thorn;er is;</L>
<L>Oure kuinde is wel hei&yogh; bicome . among alle o&thorn;ere iwis.</L>
<L N="15">Vor he is al oure kunde next . saue his god hede,<NOTE PLACE="foot">is <I>ist &uuml;bergeschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And aboute is trone men wor&thorn; next, . so noble is monhede!</L>
<L>Angles ne wor&thorn; him nout so nei&yogh;, . vor he nis heore bro&thorn;er nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>And oure kuinde is eke so hei&yogh;, . vor he ha&thorn; vs deore abou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Vor angles ne bou&yogh;te he nou&yogh;t, . we be&thorn; &thorn;er fore him &thorn;e ner;</L>
<L N="20">Whan he vs ha&thorn; so dere abou&yogh;t, . wel au&yogh;te we louen him her.</L>
<L>Angel nas neuer mo . bote as his messager;</L>
<L>How mi&yogh;te hit &thorn;anne go . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> angel were oure bro&thorn;er her?</L>
<L>And in heuene heo schulen also, . whan &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo be&thorn; &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Oure heste and oure wille do, . oure hinen as hit were,</L>
<L N="25">And to oure heste seruen vs . to fote and to honde;</L>
<L>Vor oure we mowen hem holden &thorn;us, . who so wole vnderstonde:
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="67"></L>
<L>Ne mowe &thorn;enne glade be . vorto habben such hine?<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>fehlt hinter</I> mowe.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;e so&thorn;e we mowe now iseo, . whose si&thorn; al &thorn;e fine,</L>
<L>&thorn;at we be&thorn; alre kuinde hext, . wi&thorn; oute oure lord one,</L>
<L N="30">And in heuene al so him next . among his angles echone,</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;at now late come, . se&thorn;&thorn;e oure lord ali&yogh;te</L>
<L>And oure vlesch ha&thorn; here inome, . ihered beo is mi&yogh;te!</L>
<L>And hi &thorn;at bi fore were, . whan hy &thorn;e de&thorn; afonge,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne heo were for&thorn; inome . in to helle grounde;</L>
<L N="35">Nere neuer so holi ne so god, . &thorn;er nas for bore non:</L>
<L>&thorn;er fore heo longeden in here mod . after oure lord echon.</L>
<L>&thorn;e prophetes &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> were so gode . and so holi men alle,</L>
<L>&thorn;at of oure lord vnderstode . how hit scholde bi falle,</L>
<L>Heo wusten wel &thorn;at he wolde come, . ac heo nusten whanne;</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;e time hem &thorn;ou&yogh;te swi&thorn;e long, . vnche hem &thorn;ou&yogh;te aspanne.<NOTE PLACE="foot">vch <I>fehlt vor</I> vnche.</NOTE></L>
<L>Heo gradden after him wel ofte . in here prophecie</L>
<L>And in here bokes &thorn;at heo wrou&yogh;ten, . vor he scholde hi&yogh;e.</L>
<L>God &yogh;eue, qua&thorn; on of hem, . &thorn;at heuene borste ato,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he mi&yogh;te li&yogh;te adoun anon . and vs sauie so.</L>
<L N="45">Somdel hem longede &thorn;o, . whan he ne mi&yogh;te abide,</L>
<L>&thorn;at heuene cleue softe ato . to sauen ei&thorn;er side.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hat Ms. Ash. 43 vier Verse, die hier fehlen</I>.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Par di &yogh;et ne cam he nou&yogh;t, . nere him neuer so wo,</L>
<L>Ar he hedde &thorn;e ground of helle sou&yogh;t, . he &amp; o&thorn;er mo.</L>
<L>Sein dauid ek in his anuy . after him gradde &thorn;us:</L>
<L N="50">Lord, &thorn;in heuene abowe adoun . and ali&yogh;t to vs,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Am Rande ist nebengeschrieben:</I> D(omi)ne inclina celos tuos et ostende fac(iem) t(uam) et salui erimus.</NOTE></L>
<L>And schew vs &thorn;in holi face, . &amp; we wor&thorn; sauf anon!</L>
<L>Him longede ek after his grace . &thorn;e olde symeon,</L>
<L>Vor al o&thorn;er blisse him was binome, . &amp; ofte he gradde bifore:</L>
<L>Lord, whanne wol he come? . whann wol he be bore?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> wan <I>statt</I> wanne.</NOTE></L>
<L N="55">Weneste &thorn;at ich mowe dure? . weneste &thorn;at i<SUP>c</SUP> mowe iseo?
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="69"></L>
<L>Heore mone hit was deol to here, . hem gladede no gleo;</L>
<L>Ac he menede him for nou&yogh;t . a&yogh;en o&thorn;ere bifore,</L>
<L>Vor he nas nou&yogh;t to de&thorn;e ibrou&yogh;t, . ar god were ibore,</L>
<L>Ac liuede, forte he him say . &amp; in his armes nom,<NOTE PLACE="foot">de <I>in</I> liuede <I>&uuml;bergeschrieben</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="60">&thorn;o he acondel masse day . to &thorn;e temple com.</L>
<L>Lorrd, wel may vs bet now, . &thorn;an hem mi&yogh;te &thorn;o,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> lorrd <I>st.</I> lord; <I>vor</I> bet <I>fehlt</I> beo.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at ne mi&yogh;te nou&yogh;t so fle, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he ne moste to helle go.</L>
<L>&thorn;er fore oure lord him selue seide, . &thorn;o he was on er&thorn;e ibore,</L>
<L>&thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> we mi&yogh;ten beo glade &amp; lute dede (!) . &thorn;en heo &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> weren bifore.</L>
<L N="65">&thorn;at prophetus wilneden to seo . and mankuinde al so,</L>
<L>&thorn;at we se&thorn; now, &yogh;if hit mi&yogh;te be, . ac heo mi&yogh;ten hit no&yogh;t do;</L>
<L>Vor we mowen as it were for nou&yogh;t . anon to heuene come,</L>
<L>Su&thorn;&thorn;e oure lord vs ha&thorn; i bou&yogh;t . &amp; &thorn;e deoles power binome;</L>
<L>Ac heo &thorn;at such grace nadden, . &thorn;at biforen vs come,</L>
<L N="70">After oure lowde (!) gradden . in here prophecie ilome;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> lowde <I>st.</I> lorde, <I>oder es fehlt</I> lorde <I>nach</I> lowde.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hoe gradden after him so hei&yogh;e . wi&thorn; grete wille and longe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hoe <I>st.</I> heo, <I>wie v. 626</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And non amendement ne sei&yogh;e . bote &thorn;e pine of helle stronge.</L>
<L>So longe &thorn;at heo weren weri . &amp; leten al be stille,</L>
<L>And of greding for bere . and toke al godes wille,</L>
<L N="75">Vor heo ne sei&yogh;e non o&thorn;er won, . &thorn;ei&yogh; hem &thorn;ou&yogh;te longe;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Von</I> &thorn;ei&yogh; <I>bis</I> inow&yogh; <I>77 fehlt in Ash. 43</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Oure lord lette heo (!) wille ago, . ar he wolde oure vlesch avonge.<NOTE PLACE="foot">lette <I>aus</I> hette <I>corrigirt; Ms.</I> heo <I>st.</I> heom.</NOTE></L>
<L>And &thorn;o heo weren weri inow&yogh; . as whose sei&thorn; for sore,</L>
<L>Euer vch to reste drow . &amp; speken of him namore.</L>
<L>&thorn;at swete bern oure kuinde nam . in vlesch &amp; in velle.</L>
<L N="80">Of &thorn;e kunde of wham he com . somwat imot telle.</L>
<L>A god mon &thorn;at het Isacar . was bi olde dawe</L>
<L>In bedleem, &thorn;at dou&yogh;tren to . hadde bi olde lawe:</L>
<L>&thorn;e on was anne, &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> ber . oure ledi seinte Marie,</L>
<L>&thorn;e o&thorn;er &thorn;at was sein Jones moder, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> al so marie;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Statt</I> was <I>ist jedenfalls</I> ber <I>zu lesen; hinter</I> al so <I>fehlt</I> het.</NOTE></L>
<L N="85">And elisabet ber of hire . sein Jon &thorn;e baptist,</L>
<L>And marie, anne dou&yogh;ter, . ber oure lord ih&umacr; crist.</L>
<L>A god mon &thorn;at was in galilee, . iclepud Joachim,</L>
<L>A schepherde was and holi mon, . &amp; godes grace was wi&thorn; him.
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="71"></L>
<L>&thorn;o he was of twenti winter, . seint anne he nom to wiue.<MILESTONE N="28" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="90">&thorn;er nas couple in isrl . of so clene liue.<NOTE PLACE="foot">isrl <I>Abbrv. st.</I> Israel.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e heo douteden ih&umacr; crist, . here god heo deleden a &thorn;reo</L>
<L>Vche &yogh;er, al &thorn;at heo hadden, . &thorn;at ech mon mi&yogh;te iseo.</L>
<L>&thorn;at o del heo &yogh;af to &thorn;e temple, . &thorn;at serueden &thorn;er inne,</L>
<L>As we &yogh;eue&thorn; now oure teu&thorn;inge . of &thorn;at we mowe winne;</L>
<L N="95">&thorn;at o&thorn;er del heo &yogh;af pore men . and wey uerinde al so;</L>
<L>Hem self he liueden bi &thorn;e &thorn;ridde . godes seruise to do.</L>
<L>&thorn;er fore nomon of isrl . &thorn;at so muche of orf hedde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Vor</I> nomon <I>fehlt</I> nas.</NOTE></L>
<L>As Joachim and his wif, . for &thorn;e gode lif &thorn;at heo ladden.</L>
<L>Vor whose de&thorn; is te&thorn;inge wel . loke now and &thorn;o,</L>
<L N="100">His god wol &thorn;e bctere waxe . and schal euer mo.</L>
<L>Joachim and anne is wif . to gadere here lif ladde</L>
<L>In clene spoushod twenti &yogh;er, . and nochild heo nadde.</L>
<L>Of schamed heo weren &thorn;erof sore, . vor hem &thorn;ou&yogh;ten &thorn;at heo were<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> &thorn;ou&yogh;t&emacr; <I>mit &uuml;berfl&uuml;ssigem</I> n.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vor&yogh;ete of god bi fore alle o&thorn;ere, . vor heo no child ne bere.</L>
<L N="105">Heo bi heten god, &yogh;if &thorn;at he wolde . eni child hem sende,</L>
<L>To godes seruise to oblegi . &thorn;at child wi&thorn; outen ende.</L>
<L>Ech &yogh;er also Joachim . to &thorn;e temple wende</L>
<L>&thorn;reo si&thorn;e, to stablen his bi heste, . &yogh;if god him eni child sende;</L>
<L>And offrede largeliche . of &thorn;ing &thorn;at he hadde,</L>
<L N="110">Vor schame &amp; eke for sorinesse . &thorn;at he no child nadde.</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo hadden twenti &yogh;er . ilad here lif so,</L>
<L>Joachim offrede to &thorn;e temple, . as he was woned to do.</L>
<L>&thorn;e preost &thorn;at &thorn;e temple wuste . pulte him abak anon</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;at he vn wur&thorn;e was . among gode men to gon,</L>
<L N="115">And seide &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> oure lord hit schewede wel, . whan he ne &thorn;olede nou&yogh;t</L>
<L>&thorn;at eni child as of o&thorn;er was . of hem were for&thorn; ibrou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Joachim was so sore aschomed . &thorn;at he wende out anon,</L>
<L>Vor schame among o&thorn;er men . in &thorn;e temple he nolde gon.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; his schep he wende in to ano&thorn;er lond . wepinde wel sore.</L>
<L N="120">He ne &thorn;ou&yogh;te in &thorn;e temple come . ne to anne is wif na more.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere schep herdes &thorn;er he was . in deol mon&thorn;es fiue,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he ne herde word of is frend . ne of anne is wiue.</L>
<L>An angel com adoun to him . and bad hem be li&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hem <I>st.</I> him.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="73"></L>
<L>And seide oure lord him wolde sende . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he wilnede ofte si&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="125">And &thorn;at he scholde habbe a dou&yogh;ter . of him bi &yogh;ite,</L>
<L>To ioie and blisse of alle &thorn;e world, . as &thorn;e prophetes hadden iwrite.</L>
<L>In tokninge &thorn;erof he bed him gon hom, . &yogh;if he it leue nolde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">him <I>im Ms. doppelt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>And ate goldene &yogh;ate his wyf . homward he mete scholde.</L>
<L>Joachim ne leuede him nou&yogh;t, . vo heo so longe childles were,<NOTE PLACE="foot">vo <I>st.</I> vor, <I>wie v. 361</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L N="130">Ac hamward he wende na&thorn;eles, . he ne dorste elles for fere.</L>
<L>Gret deol made anne his wif vor him, . ne mi&yogh;te no wommon more.</L>
<L>As heo was for him in morning . and wep aday wel sore</L>
<L>And gan to sike and wringe hire honden: . swete lord, heo sede,</L>
<L>Vch &thorn;ing bote vs &thorn;ow &yogh;euest ioie . and echinge of blede,</L>
<L N="135">Vs one &thorn;ow makest ioieles, . ine seo non o&thorn;er so;</L>
<L>Me wondre&thorn; &yogh;if i<SUP>c</SUP> dorste sigge . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> wolt &thorn;i wille do,</L>
<L>Whanne &thorn;ou children me binimest, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;ow me hast binome</L>
<L>Min hosbonde &thorn;at is mi ioie, . i not whar he is bicome.</L>
<L>&thorn;o com &thorn;er angel to hire; . ne doute &thorn;e nou&yogh;t! he sede,</L>
<L N="140">Ich am &thorn;e angel &thorn;at habbe ibore . bi fore god &thorn;i godhede;</L>
<L>An gode dou&yogh;ter &thorn;ou schalt bere . al &thorn;orw godes rede,</L>
<L>Marie schal hire name beo, . &thorn;at holi lif schal lede;</L>
<L>Of hire schal wondri al &thorn;e world . &amp; &thorn;orw hire isaued beo;</L>
<L>&thorn;at child &thorn;ow schalt bi time bere . and &thorn;at so&thorn;e iseo;</L>
<L N="145">A&yogh;e &thorn;in hosbonde &thorn;ow go anon, . and, to folfulle &thorn;i bone,</L>
<L>Ate goldene &yogh;ate &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> schalt him mete, . ne come &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> neuer so sone.</L>
<L>Anne ne leuede nou&yogh;t wel &thorn;is, . ac na&thorn;eles for&thorn; heo wende</L>
<L>Vorte meten hire hosbonde, . as &thorn;e angel hire sende.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a. R.</I>: Portam auream.</NOTE></L>
<L>Joachim and anne his wif . to gadere sone hem mette</L>
<L N="150">Ate guldene &yogh;ate wi&thorn; gret ioie, . as &thorn;e angel hem sette.</L>
<L>Heo clupten and custen wi&thorn; ioie inow; . &thorn;e bet heo loueden &thorn;o<NOTE PLACE="foot">loueden <I>st.</I> leueden.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vor to habben &thorn;is holi child, . hammard heo gonnen go.</L>
<L>Anne se&thorn;&thorn;e wi&thorn; childe, . and &thorn;orw ri&yogh;te kunde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Die Verse 153-273 finden sich als eigenes Gedicht auch in Ms. Bodl. 779, fol. 271 b, in dem dem Ms. vorangehenden Inhaltsverzeichnisse angegeben als</I> Seint Anne oure lady moder.</NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fehlt</I> was <I>hinter</I> childe,</NOTE></L>
<L>Ber se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;e sweete bern . &thorn;at euer wor&thorn; in muinde,</L>
<L N="155">Marie, &thorn;at vs ha&thorn; isaued . &thorn;at er were for lore.</L>
<L>&thorn;ei&yogh;te&thorn;e day of septembre . &thorn;e child was ibore.
<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="75"></L>
<L>In ierlm heo was ibore . in hire fader house iwis</L>
<L>Bi side &thorn;e &yogh;ate of iosaphat, . &thorn;er an abbey now is</L>
<L>In &thorn;e honour of oure ledi, . a blak nonnerie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Statt</I> of oure ledi <I>lesen Ash. 43 u. Bodl. 779</I> of s. anne.</NOTE></L>
<L N="160">In &thorn;e stude &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo was ibore . &thorn;e swete maide marie.</L>
<L>Holi chirche nuste nou&yogh;t . whuc day heo was ibore,</L>
<L>Ar now late &thorn;orw miracle . &thorn;at god dude  fore.</L>
<L>A god mon now late euer vch &yogh;er . gret ioie in heuene say</L>
<L>Vrom &yogh;ere to &yogh;ere in septembre, . as valle&thorn; oure ledi day.</L>
<L N="165">Oure lord he bad ententifliche . som tokne him sende &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Whi more ioie in heuene &thorn;o . &thorn;an in o&thorn;er time were.</L>
<L>An angel him seide &thorn;at oure ledi . was ibore &thorn;ulke day,</L>
<L>And of hire bur&thorn;time was al &thorn;e ioie . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> he in heuene isay;</L>
<L>And bad him warne holichurche . &thorn;at men on er&thorn;e al so</L>
<L N="170">Maden feste of &thorn;ulke day, . as he say in heuene do.</L>
<L>Hire bur&thorn;time al holichirche . wusten on &thorn;is manere.</L>
<L>Telle we now of hire lif, . &thorn;at heo ladde on er&thorn;e here!</L>
<L>Anon &thorn;o heo was &thorn;reo &yogh;er old, . as hit fel in &thorn;e lawe,</L>
<L>Offred to &thorn;e temple heo was, . as me vsede bi olde dawe,</L>
<L N="175">&thorn;o heo bi leuede hire moder breste, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> heo ne sek na more.</L>
<L>And &thorn;o heo to &thorn;e temple com, . me mi&yogh;te iseo godes ore:</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;er were viftene degres . imad bifore &thorn;e auter<MILESTONE N="29" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>In &thorn;e honuraunce of viftene salmes . &thorn;at be&thorn; in &thorn;e sauter;</L>
<L>&thorn;is maide clomb vch after o&thorn;er, . vor te heo come an hei&yogh;,</L>
<L N="180">As heo were of gret elde, . ne com hire no mon nei&yogh;;</L>
<L>Heo ne bi heold after fader ne moder, . &thorn;o heo vppard stei&yogh;.</L>
<L>Gret wonder hadde vch mon of hire . &thorn;at &thorn;is &thorn;ing isei&yogh;.</L>
<L>Chastite heo bihet al bi hire lif, . &yogh;if hit godes wille were.</L>
<L>Mid o&thorn;er maidnes in &thorn;e temple . heo was forto lere.</L>
<L N="185">So renable heo was and queinte . of wit &amp; of dede,</L>
<L>&thorn;at vch mon of a so &yogh;ong &thorn;ing . wonder hedde and drede.</L>
<L>Heo nas neuer isei&yogh;e wro&thorn; . ne enes li&yogh;ynge gon</L>
<L>Ne onus word sigge to man, . bote euer more in on.</L>
<L>Heo sewede and span and waf&yogh; . bo&thorn;e wollene and lynne,</L>
<L N="190">Heo hedde o&thorn;er lutel er&thorn;liche god . hire mete to winne.</L>
<L>Vche werke day bi ri&yogh;t time . &thorn;e day heo delede a&thorn;reo:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> b ri&yogh;t <I>st.</I> bi ri&yogh;t.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="77"></L>
<L>Ech morwe forto vnderne . in hire bedes wolde beo,<NOTE PLACE="foot">heo <I>fehlt vor</I> wolde.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vrom vnderne to midouernon . to hire werke sitte,</L>
<L>Spinne o&thorn;er sewe o&thorn;er weue, . he was gode witte;<NOTE PLACE="foot">of <I>fehlt nach</I> was.</NOTE></L>
<L N="195">In hire bedes &thorn;anne heo wolde . vort eue beo wel softe.</L>
<L>To hire an angel com alday . and confortede ofte.<NOTE PLACE="foot">hire <I>fehlt vor</I> ofte.</NOTE></L>
<L>Whan heo herde of sike men, . to hem sone heo wende</L>
<L>And confortede &amp; helede hem sone . &thorn;orw grace &thorn;at god hire sende.</L>
<L>In hire child hod al &thorn;is was . &thorn;at ichabbe of itold.</L>
<L N="200">Vor alle godne(sse) wi&thorn; hire was . bo&thorn;e &yogh;ong and old.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> godne <I>st.</I> godnesse.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;o heo was of fortene &yogh;er old, . &thorn;e bisschop of &thorn;e lawe</L>
<L>Het vche maide of &thorn;ulke elde . to hire contreie drawe,</L>
<L>To take hosbonde as lawe was; . &thorn;e maidnes were alle fawe</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e heste, bote marie, . hire likede no&yogh;t &thorn;e sawe;</L>
<L N="205">&thorn;o heo was ihote vor&thorn; . hosbonde wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere to take:</L>
<L>Sire, heo seide, &thorn;at lawe wole, . inul nowt for sake;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Vor</I> lawe <I>fehlt</I> &thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac mi fader and mi moder . bi hete for me, ar i<SUP>c</SUP> were bi&yogh;ete,</L>
<L>&thorn;at ischolde in godes seruise . mi maidenhod wite;</L>
<L>And mi seluen ek, &thorn;o ich was child, . bi het oure lord al one</L>
<L N="210">To libbe mi lif in chastite . wi&thorn; oute mannes mone;</L>
<L>&thorn;er fore isigge ow to so&thorn;e . &thorn;at &thorn;is is mi wille:</L>
<L>Nei&yogh; mon nulle i<SUP>c</SUP> neuer come . mi maiden hod to spille.</L>
<L>&thorn;e bischop and alle &thorn;e o&thorn;er maistres, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> of &thorn;e temple were,</L>
<L>Gret conseil nomen of &thorn;is word . and weren in grete fere,</L>
<L N="215">Vor &thorn;e bok wolde &thorn;at no mon . a&yogh;en such bi heste scholde be,</L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;e lawe wolde &thorn;at no wommon . from spoushod scholde vle.</L>
<L>Gret conseil &thorn;er of heo nomen, . from dai&yogh;e to dai&yogh;e were<NOTE PLACE="foot">and <I>fehlt vor</I> from.</NOTE></L>
<L>In bedes to bidde ih&umacr; crist . som tokninge hem sende &thorn;ere.</L>
<L>&thorn;o com &thorn;er avois and bad hem . &thorn;enchen on Isaye,</L>
<L N="220">And &thorn;at maide spouse chese . &thorn;orw his prophecie.</L>
<L>Now seide Isaye . &thorn;at &thorn;er scholde springe</L>
<L>A &yogh;erde of Jessees more . and of dauid &thorn;e kinge,</L>
<L>And a flour scholde vp teo . of &thorn;ilke more also,</L>
<L>And &thorn;er vpe &thorn;e holi gost . come ali&yogh;te &thorn;er to.</L>
<L N="225">Her &thorn;orw &thorn;is men wuste . how heo scholden on take.</L>
<L>Of daui&thorn;es kunne he het vche man, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> were wi&thorn; oute make
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="79"></L>
<L>And elde to habbe wif, . &thorn;at vch of hem bere<NOTE PLACE="foot">of <I>fehlt vor</I> elde.</NOTE></L>
<L>A bar &yogh;erde to &thorn;e auter, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> non vor bore nere;</L>
<L>And whos &yogh;erde bigonne to blowe . &amp; a coluere &thorn;er on ibrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="230">&thorn;at he toke marie to spouse, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> hit nere bi leued nou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&thorn;e bischop was &thorn;o glad inow, . he let crie &thorn;ere</L>
<L>&thorn;at alle &thorn;at were of daui&thorn;es kunne . a&yogh;erde to &thorn;auter bere.</L>
<L>&thorn;o heo weren alle to gadere, . &amp; vch hedde a&yogh;erde an honde:</L>
<L>&thorn;er was iosep an old mon, . &thorn;at bi hinde alle gan stonde.</L>
<L N="235">A&yogh;en his wille &thorn;ider he com, . he ne dorste elles for fere;</L>
<L>His &yogh;erde he hudde, &thorn;o his felaws . here &yogh;erden to &thorn;e auter bere.</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;er nas non &thorn;at gan to blowe, . and iosep heo vnder &yogh;ite</L>
<L>&thorn;at hedde is &yogh;erde so ihudde, . heo gonnen him to &thorn;rete;</L>
<L>Heo maden him bere is &yogh;erde for&thorn;, . he ne moste vor bore beo;</L>
<L N="240">&thorn;o he to &thorn;e auter com, . me mi&yogh;te miracle iseo:</L>
<L>His &yogh;erde bigan to blowe faire, . &thorn;at bar was and old er,</L>
<L>And anowarde sat awhit coluere; . gret miracle was &thorn;er:</L>
<L>Vpe &yogh;erde longe heo sat, . and se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;at volk isai&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e <I>fehlt vor</I> &yogh;erde.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at heo vlei&yogh; into &thorn;e temple aboute . &amp; se&thorn;&thorn;e to heuene anhei&yogh;.</L>
<L N="245">&thorn;er nas non &thorn;at &thorn;is sei&yogh;, . &thorn;at sore adrad nas.</L>
<L>Ac iosep &thorn;e olde mon is his half . &thorn;er fore sori was;</L>
<L>&thorn;at me lokede him to wedde &thorn;at maide, . of schamed he was sore.</L>
<L>Loke&thorn;, he seide, mi feblesse . and habbe&thorn; of me milse and ore!</L>
<L>Nam ich old wi&thorn; manie children? . mi mi&yogh;ten be&thorn; me bi nome,</L>
<L N="250">And heo is &yogh;ong, &amp; sunne hit is . to maken vs to gedere come.</L>
<L>Nim &yogh;eme, iosep! qua&thorn; &thorn;e bischop, . &thorn;at &thorn;ow &thorn;i self ne aspille,</L>
<L>As datan dude and abiron . &thorn;at weren a&yogh;e godes wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;o was iosep sore adrad, . he ne dorste wi&thorn; sigge na more</L>
<L>Vor drede of oure lordes wreche; . he gan to sike sore.</L>
<L N="255">I nul no&yogh;t, he seide, god misdo; . ac, whan hit mot so nede,</L>
<L>Ichul hire wedde, ac heo ne schal . hire maidenhod for me schede;</L>
<L>Ichul hire witen and hire warden, . o&thorn;er ne mai it be nou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>&thorn;at mi sone mai hire wedde after me, . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> oure kuinde be for&thorn; ibrou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;e lawe was &thorn;o : whan amon ne mi&yogh;te . bi&yogh;ete child bi is wiue,</L>
<L N="260">&thorn;at is nexte kun hire wedde scholde . anon after is liue,</L>
<L>And vch after o&thorn;er, vorte som child . of &thorn;e blode come;</L>
<L>Whose no child no wonne, vn wur&thorn;e was, . as hit fel ofte ilome.
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="81"></L>
<L>Josep weddede in &thorn;is entente . &thorn;is clene maide &thorn;ere.</L>
<L>Ac for o&thorn;er &thorn;ing oure lord wolde . &thorn;at heo wedded were:</L>
<L N="265">&thorn;at is moder isclaundred nere . wi&thorn; childe vnwedded were,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Vor</I> wi&thorn; childe <I>fehlt</I> &thorn;at heo.</NOTE><MILESTONE N="30" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ne &thorn;at &thorn;e deuel it vnder &yogh;ite . &thorn;at amaide achild bere;</L>
<L>Vor, &yogh;if he it wuste, e wolde wite . &thorn;at hit were godes sone,</L>
<L>And habbe destourbed al &thorn;e dede . of his swete passione;</L>
<L>And oure lord wolde ek &thorn;at is moder . were in eche god hod</L>
<L N="270">Of wommon, &thorn;at &thorn;reo be&thorn;: . &thorn;e hexte is maiden hod,</L>
<L>&thorn;at o&thorn;er hexte is widue hod, . spoushod is &thorn;e &thorn;ridde:</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;e &thorn;reo &thorn;at maiden hadde, . &thorn;at swi&thorn;e wel bi tidde:</L>
<L>Heo was maide, wif, and widue; . whose nis non of &thorn;e &thorn;reo,</L>
<L>Bote heo comen to amendement, . of hiren ne may he nou&yogh;t beo.</L>
<L N="275">Ac na&thorn;eles al &thorn;er wi&thorn; oute . me may &yogh;et finde some,</L>
<L>Ac, &yogh;if god wole, heo amende&thorn; hem, . ar heo to de&thorn;e come.</L>
<L>Bi eroudes day &thorn;e king . aprest was of god lif,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A. R.:</I> Fuit in diebus herodes rex; <I>s. Luc. 1, 5</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at Zakarie was ihote, . and elisabe&thorn; is wif;</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e heo weren god inow . and inelde weren igon</L>
<L N="280">And oure lordes heste douteden, . ac child nadden heo non.</L>
<L>&thorn;o scholde vch prest after o&thorn;er, . as hit fel in &thorn;e lawe,</L>
<L>Vrom saterday to saterday . aboute &thorn;e weued drawe</L>
<L>And serue &thorn;at weued al &thorn;e wike . and al &thorn;e wike be clene,</L>
<L>Ne from &thorn;e weued come nou&yogh;t, . ne seon is wif nou&yogh;t ene.</L>
<L N="285">So it bifel &thorn;at Zakarie, . as it aboute com,</L>
<L>His prestes wike scholde beo. . holi ensense e nom</L>
<L>And &thorn;er wi&thorn; wende into &thorn;e temple . and &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> weued ensensede aboute;</L>
<L>And &thorn;at volk stode in orisons . and in here bedes wi&thorn; oute.</L>
<L>In &thorn;e ri&yogh;t half of &thorn;e weued . an angel &thorn;er stod;</L>
<L N="290">Zakarie him bihuld . and dradde in his mod.</L>
<L>Ne dred &thorn;e nou&yogh;t! &thorn;e angel sede, . (&thorn;)i bone is herd anon:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> ibone <I>st.</I> &thorn;i bone.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;iwif schal bere a sone, . &thorn;at schal beo cleped Jon;</L>
<L>And &thorn;ow schalt habbe ioie inow, . whan &thorn;ow it mi&yogh;t iseo,</L>
<L>And &thorn;er schulle of his bur&thorn;time . manie glade beo;</L>
<L N="295">Bifore oure lord he wor&thorn; gret, . he ne schal drinke nou&yogh;t</L>
<L>Wyn ne sider; ar he beo . of is moder wombe ibrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>He wor&thorn; fol of &thorn;e holi gost, . and ate nende</L>
<L>Manie children of isrl . to oure lord wende.
<PB REF="00000126.tif" N="82"></L>
<L>&thorn;anne spak Zakarie: . how mi&yogh;te &thorn;is bicome?</L>
<L N="300">Vor icham old and eke mi wif, . &amp; oure kuinde is bi nome.</L>
<L>Icham, qua&thorn; &thorn;e angel, &thorn;ulke . &thorn;at to &thorn;e come in sonde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">u. 2. <I>Die letzten Halbzeilen sind umzustellen</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;e archangel gabriel . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> bi fore oure lord de&thorn; stonde;</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;ow nelt nou&yogh;t &thorn;is ileue, . &thorn;ow wor&thorn; dombe &thorn;er fore,</L>
<L>And &thorn;i speche &thorn;e bi nome, . vorte &thorn;e child be bore.</L>
<L N="305">&thorn;is angel wende for&thorn; anon, . and Zakarie &thorn;o</L>
<L>Bileuede dombe al &thorn;ilke time . and ne spak wordes na mo.</L>
<L>Euere was &thorn;e folk wi&thorn; oute . and wondrede in here &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;at Zakarie was so longe . &amp; ne com among hem nou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&thorn;o wende Zakarie out . among &thorn;is men echon</L>
<L N="310">And made signe what e wolde, . ac he ne spak word non.</L>
<L>&thorn;at volk, vor he was so dombe, . stoden alle in gret ei&yogh;e</L>
<L>And wuste wel &thorn;at wi&thorn; inne . sum si&yogh;t he hadde isei&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;o his seruise was ido . and is wike ibrou&yogh;t to ende,</L>
<L>Al dombe as he was bicome . to is wif he gan wende,</L>
<L N="315">And bi&yogh;at &thorn;at holi bern, . sein Jon &thorn;e baptist,</L>
<L>&thorn;at was alre bern best, . wi&thorn; oute ih&umacr; crist.</L>
<L>&thorn;e vif&thorn;e day he was bi&yogh;ete . bifore mi&yogh;elmasse ri&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Euene &thorn;e time &thorn;at &thorn;o was . euene day and ni&yogh;t,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> &thorn;a <I>st.</I> &thorn;e, <I>oder</I> &thorn;at <I>wie 535</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Half &yogh;er bifore &thorn;at oure lord . in his moder wombe was ali&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="320">&thorn;us was sein Jon &thorn;e baptist . bi &yogh;ete on gode ni&yogh;t.</L>
<L>And is (fader) bilafte dombe, . vor he nolde &thorn;e so&thorn;e iwite.<NOTE PLACE="foot">fader <I>fehlt im Ms</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Telle we now for&thorn; of iosep, . as hit is iwrite!</L>
<L>&thorn;o iosep hadde is wif iwedded, . as hit fel in &thorn;e lawe,</L>
<L>To ward is owne contre . to bedleem e gan drawe,</L>
<L N="325">To purueien him of bruidale, . whanne he hedde wher wi&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Zu</I> wher wi&thorn; <I>vgl. 871</I> whar of.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mid is werk and mid is craft, . vor he was smi&yogh;&thorn;.</L>
<L>Into galile to hire frendes . oure swete ledi wende</L>
<L>To nazareth, &thorn;er heo was bore, . as &thorn;e bischop hire sende,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>In v. 157 war Jerusalem als Geburtsort bezeichnet; vgl. v. 1103</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wi&thorn; maidnes of hire elde . &thorn;at hire wardeins were.</L>
<L N="330">As heo was al one in here bedes . in hire chambre &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>I send was &thorn;e angel gabriel . vrom god to &thorn;e cite,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A. R.:</I> Missus est A(ngelus), <I>s. Luc. 1, 26</I>.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="83"></L>
<L>&thorn;at is icleped nazareth, . in &thorn;e lond of galilee,</L>
<L>To amaide ispoused to amon . wi&thorn; oute vche folie</L>
<L>Of daui&thorn;es hous, &thorn;at het iosep, . &thorn;at maide het marie.</L>
<L N="335">&thorn;e angel com in to hire chambre . &amp; grette hire faire iwis:</L>
<L>Hail be &thorn;ow, fol of grace, . oure lor mid &thorn;e is;<NOTE PLACE="foot">lor <I>st.</I> lord; is <I>im Ms. doppelt</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>A mong alle wimmen iblessed be &thorn;ow, he sede.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>A. R.:</I> Aue mar(ia).</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;e maide &thorn;is iherde, . heo stod as in drede</L>
<L>And of &thorn;e angeles word . destourbed was &thorn;ere,</L>
<L N="340">And in gret &thorn;ou&yogh;te was, . what &thorn;is greting were.</L>
<L>&thorn;o nempnede vurst &thorn;e angel . hire name: marie, he sede,</L>
<L>&thorn;ow hast ifounde grace of god, . ne haue &thorn;ow none drede!</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;ow schalt in &thorn;ine wombe . conceiue wi&thorn; oute blame,</L>
<L>And a sone ibore of &thorn;e, . &thorn;at <ABBR>ihc</ABBR> schal beo is name.<NOTE PLACE="foot">beo <I>fehlt vor</I> ibore.</NOTE></L>
<L N="345">&thorn;is schal muche beo, . &amp; icleped he wor&thorn; also</L>
<L>&thorn;e hei&yogh;e godes sone, . &amp; oure lord him wole do</L>
<L>And &yogh;iue him daui&thorn;es sege, . his fader, and neuer mo,</L>
