<L N="10">Whon <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> was . of twelf &yogh;er age</L>
<L>In to &thorn;e Temple . he com to lere</L>
<L>Wrangful wrecches . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> wrou&yogh;t outrage</L>
<L>Maystres wondrede . &thorn;<SUP>t</SUP> &thorn;er were</L>
<L>&thorn;at lawes lerede . in heore langage</L>
<L N="15">And seide child . what destou &thorn;ere</L>
<L>&thorn;ou sittest stalled . in vre stage.</L>
<L>A Mayster seide . to Jh&umacr;</L>
<L>&thorn;ou scholdest lerne . and nou&yogh;t teche</L>
<L>&thorn;ou spillest speche . what seystou.</L>
<L N="20">&thorn;i wrangful wordes . worche&thorn; wreche</L>
<L>&thorn;ou repungnest in pres . a &yogh;eyn vr prou</L>
<L>As preised prophete . &thorn;e peple preche</L>
<L>Stunt a stounde . &thorn;i sawe of Gru</L>
<L>&thorn;i wit to teche . may not reche.</L>
<L N="25">&thorn;ow schuldest lerne . a. b. c</L>
<L>ffor &thorn;e fayle&thorn; . afoundement</L>
<L>&thorn;ou tellest tales . of Trinite</L>
<L>In wonderwyse . &thorn;i wit is went</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou wolt leorne . &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> miht &thorn;he</L>
<L N="30">ffor wonder wit . on &thorn;e is sent</L>
<L>Of Bales . Boote &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> miht be</L>
<L>&yogh;if &thorn;ou neore . In errour hent</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ih&umacr; seide .I. may wel se</L>
<L>&thorn;i Bok is blynt . and &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> art blent</L>
<L N="35">&thorn;ou farest foule . so &thorn;ynke&thorn; me</L>
<L>ffor lewed lore . on &thorn;e is lent.</L>
<L>Whi is a . Bi fore . b.</L>
<L>Tel me . &thorn;at spekest in present</L>
<L>Or I. schal tymeli . teche &thorn;e</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;i Reson ra&thorn;e . &thorn;e schal Repent.</L>
<L>&thorn;e Maister . wi&thorn; wel wikked wille</L>
<L>Spak in pres . of people a pliht</L>
<L><ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> art . a grameful gille,</L>
<L>I. Rede Ra&thorn;e . &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> lerne a Riht</L>
<L N="45">And bote &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> stonde . a stounde stille</L>
<L>Te Betyng Bare . &thorn;<SUP>u</SUP> schalt be diht<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ms.</I> te <I>st.</I> to.</NOTE></L>
<L>Qwa&thorn; <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> . &thorn;at is no skille</L>
<L>I. com not hider . for to fiht.</L>
<L>&YOGH;it qua&thorn; <ABBR>Jhu</ABBR> . of myn askyng</L>
<L N="50">&thorn;ou ne &yogh;iuest . non onswere</L>
<L>I. am ful Old . &thorn;eih I. be &yogh;ing</L>
<L>A. louely lore .I. wol &thorn;e lere</L>
<L>Tak &thorn;is tale . of my teching</L>
<L>A. Is prys . wi&thorn; oute pere.</L>
<L N="55">Lettre of &thorn;reo . and is o &thorn;ing</L>
<L>&thorn;reo partyes . a. ha&thorn; knet I. fere
